title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until silver knife comes out clean. 350° for about 45 or 50 minutes or until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in casserole dish.
Place sliced onions to cover beans.
Mix and heat together the vinegar and sugar until sugar melts.
Pour vinegar mixture over beans.
Add the crumbled bacon and drippings on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach quesadillas
directions: Saute cilantro, onion and garlic in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add spinach and cheese; heat until cheese is melted. Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture onto flat of tortilla.
Distribute evenly onto half of tortilla and fold in half.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Heat butter in medium skillet over medium heat.
Grill filled tortillas on each side until brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Beat eggs lightly with salt.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or frying pan and scramble eggs until they are cooked through, but still moist.
Remove to a dish, scrape the pan and heat remaining 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add rice and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes to coat with oil.
Add roast pork and scallions and stir-fry until well mixed and heated through.
Dissolve sugar in soy sauce and sprinkle over the rice.
Add the scrambled eggs, break up and distribute throughout the rice.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Cook ground chuck, onions and garlic until beef is browned and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper on waxed paper or plate.
Add beef strips and toss to coat evenly.
Put oil into a shallow 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish; microwave on High for 1 minute or until oil is very hot.
Scatter meat strips over bottom of baking dish; microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring twice, until meat is no longer pink.

title: aunt bea's o-so good fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off chunk pineapple and add enough water to it to equal 2 cups liquid.
Add liquid to pudding in saucepan.
Cook according to pudding directions.
Cool.
Then fold in fruit. Chill until ready to serve.

title: spaghetti and pot roast(serves 4)
directions: Make 4 slits in roast and insert quarter of garlic in each. Tie meat, if necessary.
Heat oil and butter in large kettle. Brown meat slowly on all sides.
Remove meat and lower heat.
Add garlic, onion, oregano, thyme, basil, cinnamon, salt and pepper. Cook gently about 5 minutes, being careful not to burn.
Return meat.

title: no fail pie crust(5 crusts)
directions: Cut flour, shortening and salt together.
Add cold water, egg and vinegar.
Mix together.
Roll out and bake as directed.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water and salt about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Meanwhile, saute the onion in the butter until tender.
When potatoes are cooked, stir in onion, corn, pimento, milk, half and half, brown sugar, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer or until soup is slightly thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Spray two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans with nonstick coating, dust lightly with flour and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1 3/4 cups sugar, cocoa powder and soda.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Beat on low speed 30 seconds or until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Wash the beaters.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cornmeal and flour; mix.
Beat eggs and blend in sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix nuts, butter and coconut.
Mix well. Add Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: italian bread dip
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Mix with sour cream, mayonnaise, onion and seasoning.
Refrigerate 4 or more hours.
Hollow out bread loaves.
Fill with mix.
Cut hollowed out bread into bite-size pieces for dipping.

title: the ultimate chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, flours and cinnamon in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour hot mixture into dry mixture, mixing well.
In a small bowl combine buttermilk, soda, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Mix well by hand.
A wire whisk works well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add tea (loose or bags as desired) and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and add sugar.
Using 2 1/2 cups syrup to make 1 gallon of tea.

title: cathy's banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Beat eggs lightly and add a little of the hot mixture to them.
Blend well and pour into saucepan.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, for a few minutes; add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Cover pudding and cool slightly.
Arrange vanilla wafers along the bottom of casserole dish.
Alternate with layers of banana slices and pudding, ending with pudding on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Sift confectioners sugar and cocoa together.
Melt butter or oleo and Velveeta cheese in double boiler (or carefully in microwave).
Pour cheese mixture over sugar and cocoa mixture. Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into lightly buttered pan. Smooth and creamy, no cheese taste.

title: mom's popular baked rice
directions: Mix rice, water and salt and slowly bring to boil.
Cover pan and simmer about 15 minutes until all water is absorbed.
Cook raisins to boiling in 1 cup of water.
Remove from heat and let set while preparing custard.

title: spanish stew
directions: Place in slow cooker (medium setting) 7 1/2 to 8 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Mix flour and shortening in a pot.
Stir over medium heat, making a roux.
Add garlic; cook until golden brown.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until they are transparent.
Add shrimp and tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in water and blend well.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; cover with mushrooms and chestnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top. Combine undiluted soups and pimiento; pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, crumble crust; toss with butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Thaw artichokes, drain and chop.
Add cheese and mayonnaise and bake in greased casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: russian torte
directions: Combine ground nuts, 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Measure 1 cup of mixture; set aside for top.

title: superior apple butter
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and cook slowly until very thick, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Pour in jars; seal or refrigerate.

title: phyllis george's rice pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Insert this dish into another larger dish and fill with water. Bake until a knife comes out clean when inserted into the pudding.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and salt.
Combine the buttermilk and soda.
Add milk to flour; stir.
Combine the eggs and melted butter.
Add this to batter.
Stir just enough to get lumps out. Pour onto greased hot black skillet.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oleo, half and half and velveeta cheese in saucepan. Pour sauce over thawed potatoes. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Arrange zucchini on rack of a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Broil 3 inches from heat until browned, turning after 2 minutes. Combine cottage cheese, egg substitute, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, milk and pepper in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.

title: cranberry whip
directions: Blend all together adding marshmallows last.
Salad freezes well.

title: bread and butter pickles("the best")
directions: Mix salt and water; pour over pickles.
Soak for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: In a small saucepan, cook pineapple, egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar.
Meanwhile, dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Mix into cooked mixture.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into cooled mixture.
Place in baked shell and refrigerate.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased dish. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom-swiss burgers
directions: Patty the ground beef into hamburgers.
Cook until well done. Put onto buns; top with remaining ingredients.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Cool before frosting.

title: sour cream cranberry cake
directions: Combine margarine/butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add sour cream, vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour half of batter into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Spread one 8 ounce can of whole cranberry sauce over batter.
Add the other half of the batter.

title: no peeky stew
directions: Throw all ingredients into a pot with a tight-fitting lid or a Pyrex baking dish that you can cover well and tight with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not peek!
Serve over noodles.
(I frequently double the recipe.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and bananas.
Mix well.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese strata
directions: Mix butter, garlic and mustard; spread on one side of each bread slice.
Cut each slice into thirds.
Line the bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with some of bread with the buttered side down.
Mix cheese, onion, parsley, salt, Worcestershire and pepper; spread evenly over bread.
Top with remaining bread with buttered side up.
Beat eggs and blend in the milk and wine.
Pour over the bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In a 3 1/2, 4, 5 or 6 quart crockery cooker, stir together undrained tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low heat 10 to 12 hours or high heat 5 to 6 hours.
Before serving, remove bay leaf and stir well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red snapper
directions: Make dark brown roux of oil and flour.
Add onions, garlic and celery; cook until soft.
Then add tomatoes, bay leaves, thyme, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Clean red snapper and place in oblong pan.
Pour sauce over fish and bake in 350° oven, until fish is easily pierced with fork, about 30 minutes.
Baste fish with sauce throughout cooking time.
This recipe makes about a quart of sauce.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: pineapple-rice compote(cereal)
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together undrained pineapple, orange juice, brown sugar and allspice.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and stir in rice.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Transfer into 4 serving bowls.
Sprinkle with additional allspice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook in boiling, salted water; drain.
While still warm, combine spaghetti with eggs and Parmesan.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch plate; pat mixture up around sides.
Melt butter; saute onion until limp.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon over spaghetti.
Remove sausage from casing; crumble and cook.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Spoon sausage on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add Mozzarella.
Return to oven until melted.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make sugar cookie dough and bake in shape of pizza crust and let cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on pizza crust.
Refrigerate spread canned pie filling, add fruits as desired.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple, juice, and gelatin until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Cool mixture and add buttermilk and cool whip.
May add nuts.
Chill.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 onion soup mix.
Mix all other ingredients together; put in pan. Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with rest of onion soup mix.
Seal pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients all together and pour into pan.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients but the boiling water and soda.
Add it last.
Do not add any more flour. Pour in greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Use favorite topping or icing.

title: stuffed wieners
directions: Split wieners longways and stuff with leftover or fresh mashed potatoes.
Place strips of cheese on the potatoes and put into oven.
Bake at 400°; let heat through and melt cheese.
A good way to use up leftover mashed potatoes.

title: white wine cake
directions: Mix everything except nuts.
Put the nuts in a little cake batter and put on bottom of pan.
Pour mixture over the nuts and bake for 1 hour plus 10 minutes if necessary at 350°.

title: pear preserves
directions: Boil juice and sugar 5 minutes.
Add fruit to partly cooled syrup.
Bring gently to boil.
Add lemon.
Boil rapidly until clear and tender.
Let cool rapidly.
Let stand in syrup to plump.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut oleo into

Bisquick and 2 tablespoons sugar until it makes fine crumbs. Pat into a 9 x 9 x 2 square pan. Bake 10 minutes. Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and flour in a bowl until creamy. Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake until knife inserted comes out clean (55 minutes). Immediately spread on topping.

title: baked sausage stuffing(beryl)
directions: Cook sausage, onion and celery until meat and vegetables are tender.
Pour off drippings reserved.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter. Mix bread, beaten eggs and broth.
Place in a 2-quart
casserole. Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.

title: cheese muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Do not use liners.
Mix dry ingredients and 3/4 cup cheese.
Stir in liquid with fork; mix gently.
Fill muffin tins and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
These are excellent served with soup and salad.
Yield:

title: gourmet tuna patties
directions: Mix tuna, Ricotta, egg, onion, Parmesan and 3 tablespoons crumbs.
Form patties, 3 or 4.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet; coat patties in bread crumbs and brown in skillet.
Drain on brown paper.

title: ham balls
directions: Can substitute turkey for ground beef.
Mix together meats, eggs, juice, onion, green pepper and oatmeal.
Shape into balls or use an ice cream scoop.
Place in pan and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 250°.

title: buttermilk bran muffins
directions: Mix Nabisco Bran with boiling water; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix in a large, large bowl.
Keep in covered container in refrigerator, using when needed.
When you want to use, do not stir.
Just dip out and fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter keeps 2 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: ravioli with vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan and saute onion, garlic, carrot, broccoli, mushrooms and green pepper until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients except cream and cheese; let simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: grandma henry cookies(unbaked chocolate cookies)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pan.
Heat and cook until mixture boils 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: dump cake
directions: Put 2 sticks oleo, cut in squares, into an oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump the pineapple and juice.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Dump coconut over pineapple.
Spread evenly.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle nuts evenly.
Top with dry cake mix.
Spread evenly.
Do not stir.
Cover with strips of oleo.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Flip upside-down when you serve.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with cupcake papers.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Beat together sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla until smooth, at least 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with fruit pie filling, fruit or jam.
Keep chilled.

title: nana's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess grease.
In a blender put stewed tomatoes, onion and chili powder.
Combine meat and blender mixture in a big cooking pot.
Add V8 juice; fill juice cans and tomato cans with water and add to pot mixture, then add chili beans, kidney beans, spaghetti, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through.

title: chinese string beans
directions: Mix together and heat in casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones.
Cut up in chunks.
Chop eggs and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven barbeque chicken
directions: Preheat oven to
moderate
Place
chicken
skin side up on a rack in a
large shallow pan. Bake for 30 minutes. Saute onion in margarine
until
golden.
Add ketchup, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Bring to a
boil
and
simmer for 5 minutes. Remove chicken from oven and turn pieces skin side down.
Spoon some sauce over chicken and
bake
for
minutes more.
Turn pieces skin side up and
spoon
remaining
sauce
over chicken. Bake 15 minutes more.
Increase oven
heat to 425° and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries (not drained), pineapple (drained), pecans, diced bananas and Cool Whip.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze overnight.
Set out about 30 minutes before serving.

title: red satin punch
directions: Chill apple juice and cranberry juice until icy.
Combine with cold 7-Up just before serving.

title: camper stew(for those coooold winter nights or a fall camping trip.)
directions: You will need 1 huge cooking pot.

title: christmas aroma
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Simmer for fragrance.
Store in refrigerator for later use.
Add equal amount of water, apple and pineapple juice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce and raspberry jello in a bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers and applesauce mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pickled beans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Cook beans and let cool.
Fill jars to 1/2 inch from top.
Stir liquid; pour over beans and seal.
Makes 11 quarts.
Store in a cool place.

title: brussels sprouts and carrots
directions: Heat
oven
to
350°.	Combine
Brussels
sprouts
and carrots in	ungreased
to 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake until Brussels sprouts are tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix butter, lemon juice and salt; drizzle on vegetables.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mexican corn bread and whipped butter
directions: Mix muffin mix as directed.
Stir in peppers.
Bake as directed.

title: german chicken supreme
directions: Combine everything except butter, bread crumbs and shortening. Allow chicken to marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Chicken will be very heavy with sour cream so have plenty of bread crumbs ready.
Melt butter and shortening; pour half over chicken and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 325°.
Add remaining butter.
Mix and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Good with rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put ingredients into a bowl and mix.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix tangerine juice with 1 1/2 cups water and freeze in ice cube trays ahead of time.
Mix lemonade and orange juice with 4 1/2 cups water and pour into punch bowl.
Add 1 tray of regular ice cubes and the tray of tangerine ice cubes.
Add strawberries (thawed) and ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 3 quarts, 15 servings.

title: jiffy spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef, fat and onion until brown.
Combine all other ingredients except spaghetti.
Cook until desired thickness. I add 1/3 cup water.
Serves 6.

title: lentil nut loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° in oiled casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turnip green soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, add water until solid ingredients are covered.
Bring to a boil and then cover and simmer for 3 hours.
This is great served with baked sweet potato and cornbread.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix gelatin as directed on box. Set aside to cool. Mix in blender the softened cream cheese until creamy. Add nuts; mix thoroughly. Then add celery and stir. Slowly add gelatin and mix together thoroughly. Pour into container and chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add liquids slowly; stir until mixed.
Then add margarine and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites to make meringue.
Top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: baked game hens with vegetables
directions: Rinse hen halves and pat dry.
Place skin side up, down center of a shallow 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Mix lemon juice, oil, rosemary and garlic and pour over hens.
Cut unpeeled shallots in half lengthwise.
Arrange shallots, cut side down, carrots and potatoes evenly around hens.
Bake in a 450° oven until vegetables are tender when pierced and meat near thigh bone is not pink, about 35 minutes.
Transfer hens and vegetables to a warm platter. Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley sprigs.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Chop dried beef, onion and nuts in blender, then mix everything with mixer.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: candied yams
directions: Cut yams in halves. Blend butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Spread over yams.
Bake in 350° oven until hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients, saving some stuffing for topping.
Put in casserole and bake until bubbly.

title: frosting
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time.
Add milk as needed.
Mix in vanilla.
Should be soft and creamy.
Great for Christmas cookies.

title: mushroom puffs
directions: Flatten one biscuit at a time. Spread with cream cheese. Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Chop mushrooms as small as possible.
Roll up biscuits into a log and slice into 5 pieces. Lay on cookie sheet.
After all biscuits are rolled and cut, brush with milk or egg white and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll out bread dough into rectangle.
Fry sausage and drain. Sprinkle 1/2 over dough.
Shred hot pepper cheese and mix with Mozzarella and parsley flakes.
Spread over sausage.
Then spread rest of sausage over cheese mixture.
Beat eggs and drizzle over mixture.
Roll dough up jelly roll fashion.
Spread some egg mixture over top.
Place on greased cookie sheet, seam side down. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes wonderfully.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, half the flour, sugar and shortening.
Beat with spoon until smooth and batter
falls
in
sheets from spoon.
Using hands, mix in enough flour
to clean bowl with dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth and blistered.
Shape
as desired; let rise about 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed on box; poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Pour Eagle Brand over top of cake and in holes.
Pour caramel ice cream topping over cake in same manner.
Cool.
Spread whipped topping over cake. Sprinkle with Heath bits.
Let set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: cheesy oven potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup melted oleo and 1 cup corn flakes, mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vermont cheese soup
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in butter for 5 minutes. Add hot water and chicken broth and heat to boiling. Boil gently one minute. Add cheese and half and half and mix well. Heat to boiling. Stir until cheese is melted. Makes one gallon.

title: pear honey
directions: Dissolve sugar in juice from pears and pineapple.
Add pears while it is boiling; cook until done.
Add pineapple and cook 5 more minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes.
Fry in oil in large skillet. Add onions and simmer about 5 minutes.
Then add all peppers, mushrooms, pimentos and Polish sausages.
Simmer on medium heat until done.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add next 4 ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stove top macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain macaroni.
Add margarine, beaten eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until margarine is melted, then add milk.
Return to stove on simmer, constantly stirring.
Let it get hot enough to melt cheese.
Turn off burner.
Add cheese, let cheese melt.
Ready to serve.

title: three day brisket
directions: You will need aluminum foil.
Pierce meat several times on both sides. Rub with salt and soy sauce. Wrap in foil; put in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley dressing and Miracle Whip.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Use any kind of vegetables, cheese and pepperoni.
Grind or cut up and put it on top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat oil and garlic in small saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 20 minutes or the longer the better.

title: sweet-sour sauce for brown rice
directions: Mix cornstarch in the cold water.
Save tomato and mix rest of ingredients.
Add tomato and pour over cooked rice.

title: taco salad ii
directions: Add taco seasoning to ground beef per instructions on package. Chill ground beef until ready to use. In medium bowl, blend cream cheese, sour cream and dip mix. Spread this mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle seasoned ground beef on top. Finish by topping with cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and onion. Allow to chill for at least 3 hours before serving. Serve with nachos.

title: graham cracker peanut butter eggs
directions: Melt margarine; add cracker crumbs, sugar and peanut butter. Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Remove from refrigerator and shape into medium size eggs.
Chill again until firm.
Melt chocolate. Using a toothpick, dip eggs into chocolate to coat.
Place eggs on cookie sheet and chill until firm.
(Makes about 60 medium size eggs.)

title: granny's hot slaw
directions: Combine egg, flour, salt and pepper in small bowl; beat well. Heat vinegar in saucepan.
Stir in flour mixture slowly.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup white sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream remaining 1 cup white sugar with eggs, oleo and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix slowly 1/2 flour mix and 1/2 sour cream into creamed mixture.
After well mixed, add balance of flour mix and sour cream.

title: marinated tomatoes with fettuccine
directions: Toss together the chopped tomatoes, parsley, olive oil, garlic, basil and pepper; cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Cook fettuccine in boiling water until al dente; drain.
Gently toss tomato mixture with fettuccine until well combined.
Makes 8 side-dish servings.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all fruit together (pineapple and mandarin oranges, cut in halves). Pour peach pie filling over the fruit and stir until mixed. Add sliced strawberries last. Chill before serving. Serves 6.

title: deluxe strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake in oblong Pyrex pan.
When cake is cooled, add a layer of strawberries, sliced.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Add cream cheese (beaten) to the pudding.
Add a layer of pudding and cream cheese over strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip topping and keep in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cut 1/2-inch layer off top of cake.
Scoop out inside of cake and crumble it.
Mix jello with one cup boiling water.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with foil liners.
Place vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed. Add eggs and mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Top with fruit preserves.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Spray an 8-inch pie plate with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.

title: potato-bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onion in drippings.
Remove onion and drain on paper towel.
Cube potatoes and cook in the 1 cup of water.
Add soup, onion, bacon, sour cream and milk, plus seasonings, saving some bacon to crumble on top.
Simmer, but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: crackling cookies
directions: Mix the soda with the molasses and combine with other ingredients, adding enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Put by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gianna's strawberries
directions: Take your strawberries and wash them.
Cut them and put in bowl with sugar.
Mix it.
Cover it and put in refrigerator.
Eat it later.

title: stuffed taco taters
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool, cut into halves and scoop out insides, leaving skins intact.
Fry chopped onions and chop meat.
Drain fat and prepare with taco mix, following package directions.
Add scooped out potatoes (insides) to meat. Re-fill potato skins with mixture.
Bake again the filled skins for 15 minutes.
Remove and top with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts, then top with sour cream and chives.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain.
Rinse well with cold water.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Refrigerate several hours.

title: rock garden
directions: Mix bluing, ammonia and water for solution.
In a glass container, place a damp sponge.
Soak brick chips, then wipe them off.
Remove sponge.
Drip food coloring on chips and put them in glass container.
Pour solution into glass container over chips. Sprinkle with salt every 1 or 2 days and watch the garden grow.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until golden.
Combine soup, cheese and water.
Thaw broccoli; cook well.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Bake bread, cut in 7 strips, at 200° for 1 hour.
After bread is baked, dip in peanut butter and oil that has been warmed just enough to mix well.
Roll in cracker crumbs to coat or shake in plastic bag with cracker crumbs.
These are good party treats.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Mix chicken with refried beans, picante sauce, taco seasoning and cheese.
Place a spoonful in the middle of the tortilla shell, fold over.
Place in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until tortillas are brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick softened butter.
Press into pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 stick softened butter and 2 eggs. Spread on crust.
Slice bananas.
Use enough to cover sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed.
Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Place mixture on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese melts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out excess moisture.
Mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
(I usually make it the night before so the seasonings will blend.)
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat; when it becomes bubbly, cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir small amount hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to heat and cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir well, then add coconut.
Mix up.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Top with meringue before baking.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in casserole dish.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Season meat with chili powder, salt and pepper. Brown meat and drain.
Put flour tortillas on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add all ground beef, then beans, cheese and another layer of tortillas, soup, Ro-Tel and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Cut garlic lengthwise and stuff into slits in both sides of the roast.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish and butter.
Cook and drain sausage; put over bread. Add cheese, milk, eggs, salt and mustard over sausage.
Sprinkle extra cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Layer oleo, brown sugar and pineapple slices in 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cream Crisco and sugar; then add beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat well and pour over pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown meat; put in crock-pot or a large pot.
Stir and simmer for several hours.
Good with cornbread or tostadas.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well. Pour into pie crusts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: green punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until
dissolved; add lime Jell-O. Allow to cool (strain if	necessary).
Add
remaining ingredients.
If golden punch is desired, use lemon Jell-O instead of lime.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, syrup and cream of tartar for 5 minutes in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add soda; stir well.
(Use a buttered aluminum dishpan to hold popcorn.) Pour heated mixture over popped corn, mixing well to coat.
Place in a 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir popped corn often.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Position 2 racks to divide the oven into thirds and preheat to 375°.
Line cookie sheets with baking parchment or aluminum foil, shiny side up.
Cream the butter with the sugars until fluffy. Add the egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in the nuts and chocolate morsels.
You can chill the dough for at least 1 hour at this point to make it easier to handle.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except linguine, in a blender; blend together using low speed with 1/2 cup oil.
Stop every few seconds to scrape the sides of the blender down until everything is evenly mixed.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup oil in a steady stream; blend to a smooth consistency.

title: low calorie fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended and chill.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit kabobs.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Contains 20 calories per tablespoon.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Smother okra, onions and green pepper in bacon fat.
Add tomato sauce when okra is almost cooked.
Add water, peppers, green onions, bay leaf, garlic and salt.
Heat to boiling and cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes. Serve with rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add rice, milk, soup, broccoli, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well until broccoli is thawed.
Place in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brown top if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add all ingredients in a saucepan. Cook 20 minutes.
Makes a delicious side dish.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; arrange in 8-inch square baking dish. Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, cheese and marjoram. Pour over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with paprika.

title: frooj
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with margarine.
Put all ingredients except nuts into a saucepan.
Stir to boiling and cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and beat with a wooden spoon until thick and creamy.
Add nuts and pour into greased pan.
Mark in squares and cool.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and jello.
Add water and oil.
Stir eggs in one at a time.
Add strawberries with juice, beat well. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done when toothpick is inserted in middle of cake and comes out clean.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Crush Fritos.
Mix ground beef while hot with chili beans and hominy.
Mix in Fritos and cheese. Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Use a straw to punch holes 3-inches apart in a baked 9 x 13-inch size yellow or white cake.
Mix jello according to directions.
Do not chill.
Slowly pour liquid jello over cake. Cake will be soggy.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Ice with Dream Whip before serving.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin and dry ingredients, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts. Bake on large cookie sheet that has been well greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Spread on a cream cheese frosting when cooled.

title: mound roll
directions: Put potatoes in bowl.
Mix in sugar, coconut, margarine and vanilla to form stiff mixture.
Shape in roll; spread melted chocolate on roll and chill.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.
Makes about 2 cups. For Christmas, cut wreath shape out of cardboard.
Cover with foil.
In mound, spread to shape.
Garnish with pimento or cocktail tomatoes.
(If you like, maybe some fresh parsley would look nice.)

title: holiday cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and 1 cup brown sugar; cream well. Add 1 cup flour and blend.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and vanilla to eggs and beat until thick and foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder; blend well.
Add coconut and nuts. Spread over first mixture and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: baked corn(corn pudding)
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add flour and milk. Continue to stir until thick. Remove from heat. Add corn, eggs, salt, pepper and sugar. Mix well and pour
into a baking dish. Bake at 375° until brown on top, about 45 minutes.

title: tangy breaded pork chops
directions: In a shallow dish, beat together egg, garlic and mustard with fork until well blended.
Drop chops in egg mixture, then in crumbs to coat well.
In large, heavy skillet over moderate heat (or electric frypan), cook chops in oil, turning once, for 20 minutes or until browned and no longer pink inside.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Syrup:
In saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 2 cups water.
Boil; reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine.
Set aside.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, water, onion, salts and pepper together and shape into meatballs.
Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in large skillet and brown.
Drain off fat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add steak. Cook until browned, turning as needed. Transfer to plate.
Add onions to skillet.
Saute until softened. Return steak to skillet.
Add mushrooms, tossing gently. Cook 3 to 4 minutes. Reduce heat. Add sour cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated through (do not boil).
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	as
directed
and drain.
Mix all other ingredients
and
mix
with
broccoli
and	pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered Ritz crackers and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries; reserve 1/2 cup of cherry juice.
Combine reserved cherry juice, cornstarch, sugar substitute, almond extract and salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened, though the mixture will not be clear.
Add a few drops of red food color, fold in cherries and allow to rest while making pie crust.
Pour cherry filling into pie shell.
Place pie crust on top.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done. Yield:
8 servings.
Calories per serving 58.

title: old fashioned soft cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla, then alternate milk and other dry ingredients.
"Pat" dough out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with large cookie cutter or glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until slightly brown on bottom.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, mix soup and milk together until well blended. Add drained green beans, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Stir.
Spray small casserole dish with cooking spray.
Spread mixture evenly in dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Continue to bake until onions on top are browned slightly.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill before serving.

title: strawberry rhubarb-pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and flour.
Mix lightly through rhubarb and strawberries.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust with slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits.
Cover edges with 1 1/2-inch strips of aluminum foil if crust is getting too brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Put in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven to 250°.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes. Serves 5 or 6.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spread to cover entire pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Pour on top of the first mix.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 325° oven (preheated). Let cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs. Beat well. Add soda to buttermilk and flour. Beat well. Add bananas and nuts. Pour into greased pan. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caesar salad
directions: Whisk raw egg, garlic, lemon juice and oil together in the bottom of a large salad bowl.
Add lettuce and hard-boiled eggs. Toss gently.
Add cheese and toss again.
Serve with croutons and anchovies, if desired.
Add fresh ground pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sweet potatoes, honey and oil in a large bowl until blended.
Sift dry ingredients together in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients and yogurt to potato mixture. Mix by hand until soft dough is formed.
Do not overmix.
Place dough on floured surface and roll to 1/2-inch thickness or make large, Texas drop type biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until browned.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Slice pork into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices, keeping each 2 consecutive cuts together.
The size of your baking dish will be determined by the number of "sandwiches" you have.
Lay one slice of pork in baking dish.
Cover with layer of dressing mix and lay other slice of pork on top.
Continue until all "sandwiches" are done.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for about 60 minutes. Uncover and smooth mushroom soup over all.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes uncovered.
Size of loin determines number of servings.

title: paulette's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar.
Add brown sugar to sweeten to taste.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 1 month or more.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine corn bread mix and sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, milk and oil, mixing well.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning and put in a Pyrex dish.
Spread with sour cream.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: ranch crackle
directions: Put crackers in a bowl.
Sprinkle crackers with oil and stir until well coated.
Sprinkle crackers with Ranch dressing mix (dry) and stir until well coated.
Put in an airtight container and let sit overnight.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to make 3 quarts of broth.
Mix together onion, tomato, celery, garlic and scallions.
Fry in oil or margarine until clear.
Slice tortillas into 1/2-inch wide strips and fry until crisp.
Drain.
Add onion-tomato mix to broth with enough tortilla strips to flavor (save most for later, so they don't get soggy).
Add salt, pepper, comino and seasoned salt.
If broth is thin, add a bouillon cube.
Cook on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cilantro, chile verde and jalapeno juice.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
(You can use strips of chicken or just broth.)
To serve, put a small amount of grated cheese in bottom of bowl.
Add soup and sprinkle crispy tortilla chips on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and add tomato juice or tomato soup until of the right consistency.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, salad oil and eggs; mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans, greased and floured, at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: see's fudge
directions: In a large kettle, bring the milk and sugar to a rolling boil and boil exactly 10 minutes.
Be sure to stir constantly or it will stick.
Remove from
heat.
Pour over oleo, nuts, Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until all ingredients are melted.
Pour into 3 buttered cake tins.
When cool, cut into squares.
This recipe yields 5 pounds.

title: cracked wheat salad
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water and bulgur.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until water is absorbed and bulgur is tender, but not mushy.
Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate, uncovered, until cool.
Add pecans, currants, parsley, olive oil, orange zest, salt and pepper to taste.
Toss thoroughly.
Serve cool or at room temperature. Serves 8.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg, milk, half of the cracker crumbs, chili powder, salt, Worcestershire sauce and ground beef. Mix well.
Make patties, about 1 or 2-inches thick.
Coat with cracker crumbs. Cook in hot oil over medium heat until done.

title: tasty lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour and sugar gradually.
Add flour and sugar to beaten eggs.
Add lemon juice.
Add butter; heat, then add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: This makes 6 to 9 servings.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
In large bowl, beat egg and cinnamon; add remaining ingredients except Butter Rum Sauce.
Pour evenly over bread cubes, moistening completely.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm with Butter Rum Sauce.

title: caramel fluff topping
directions: Chill bowl and beaters.
Whip all ingredients together.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: easy chicken parm
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Wash berries.
Remove hulls and crush 1 cup of the smaller berries and cook with the water for about 2 minutes.

title: bristo roasted chicken
directions: Position a rack in the upper third of the oven and preheat to 475°. Season the cavity of the chicken with salt and pepper and place in a large baking pan. In a small bowl, combine the olive oil, rosemary, thyme, oregano and garlic and stir until well blended. Spread this mixture all over the skin side of the chicken and season generously with salt and pepper.

title: stifado
directions: Heat the oil in a Dutch oven and brown the meat.
Remove the meat.
Add onion and garlic; stir 5 minutes.
Add wine, vinegar, brown sugar and tomato paste.
Stir until smooth.
Add cumin, cloves, bay leaves and cinnamon.
Add meat, orange zest and currants.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a simmer. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for one hour.

title: uptown bouquet
directions: Combine vegetables and pour remaining ingredients over all. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mushroom soup, celery, water chestnuts, chicken, rice, and onion and put in casserole dish.
Top with crackers then almonds.
Drizzle melted butter on top and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly in center.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to boil to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and onion to boiled mixture.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to liquid.
Pour mixture into large greased mold.
Chill.

title: old country supper
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan, saving grease.
Slice and saute the potatoes, broccoli, carrots and onion until tender. Top with smoked sausage.
Heat 12 minutes, covered.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: sunshine orange punch
directions: Heat 1 cup of the punch and use it to dissolve the gelatin. Add mace.
Stir in remaining punch and chill until ready to serve. Add ice cream just before serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; save 2 cups of broth.
Lay deboned chicken in a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Cream together flour and softened margarine.
Blend in milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake until brown, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cookie's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, peppers, soups and sour cream.
Spread thin layer of mix in bottom of an 8 x 13-inch pan. Put 1 tablespoon of mix in each tortilla and roll. Place close together in pan. Top with remaining mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine crushed Oreo cookies and melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften peanut butter in microwave and spread over crushed cookies.
After ice cream has set out for 15 to 20 minutes, spread over top.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or colored sprinkles as desired.
Refreeze before serving.

title: egg-n-cheese strata
directions: Butter bread and cut in
small cubes.
Alternate layers of bread cubes and cheese in buttered
2 quart casserole dish. Blend together eggs, milk and
seasonings.
Pour
egg
mixture over bread-cheese mixture.
Cover
and
refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain
beets well; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients to	make
a
dressing.
Add beets to dressing; marinate for several hours.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix ingredients from the two bowls together. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks, food color and lemon juice together. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Put in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool to room temperature.
Put Cool Whip on pie when cooled.
Place in freezer until firm.

title: felafel
directions: Mash chickpeas in a bowl with a potato masher.
Add the next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Form into 12 small patties.
Heat about 1/2-inch (2 cm) oil in a skillet.
Fry the felatel on both sides until brown and crispy.
Drain on paper towels.

title: iroquois corn soup
directions: In a large 12-inch saucepan, place the mushrooms, consomme, cornmeal, cilantro, garlic, basil, onion, pepper and salt.
Simmer over medium heat, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Add the flounder, lima beans and sherry and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally and breaking the flounder into bite size pieces.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter. Add onions and sear for 2 minutes. Add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk and cheese. Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth and thickened. Add sour cream. Pour mixture over cooked macaroni. Pour in baking dish and cook (uncovered) for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepper pickles
directions: Be sure you
get
peppers
with
thick	meal.
They are heavy. Wash peppers.
Cut and take out seeds.
Slice and soak in salt water 4 to	5 hours, about 1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon of water. Rinse and heat
in	pure
vinegar
until
hot.
Put in jars.
Heat 1 cup
vinegar
and
1 cup sugar to your taste and pour over them; seal.

title: nut rolls(yields 4 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk; set aside.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add butter or margarine to flour mixture and crumble as for pie dough.
Add the dissolved yeast and eggs. Knead lightly, adding small amounts of flour to dough, if needed. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Place a layer of tomatoes (if juicy, drain on paper towel for better results) and a layer of onions in the unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with bell pepper.
Repeat layers until the pie is to the top of crust.
Mix mayonnaise and grated cheese together and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes. Baking time may vary so check after an hour and frequently until done.
With variation in tomatoes it may take 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time (beat well after each egg).
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, apple butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Blend in eggs and milk; pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: "souper" shrimp creole
directions: Skin and disjoint rabbit.
Marinate overnight in enough red wine to cover, two pods garlic, olive oil, spices and a little thyme and bay leaf.
Make a roux and in it fry rabbit pieces. Simmer for 1 hour or until tender on a slow fire with some of the strained marinade.
Serves 4.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done and drain; place half of macaroni in casserole.	Combine celery soup and milk; heat to boiling point. Arrange tuna on the macaroni and sprinkle cheese on top.
Add the rest of the macaroni; add pimento to celery soup and pour over macaroni easing it down with a fork.
Put on bread crumbs.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
One can substitute 2 cups cubed ham for tuna.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken chalupas(little boats)
directions: Bake chicken in 300° or 350° oven for 40 minutes, basting with butter. When cool enough to handle, skin, bone and dice chicken. Combine soup, chilies, sour cream, olives, onions and some of the cheese. Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this mixture. Add chicken to the rest.

title: grape or blackberry jelly
directions: Place snapped green beans in 10-quart dishpan. Add 2 cups sugar and 2 cups vinegar. Cover with enough water to cover the beans. Bring to rolling boil. Boil 40 minutes. Pack beans in jars and seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Cool before adding to egg whites, vanilla, salt and 6 tablespoons sugar.

title: cherry chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Fold in pie filling, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: amazing rice
directions: Mix rice and soups in a tight lid casserole.
Put butter in middle, don't stir.
Cover. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Fluff or not before serving.

title: do not peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly over a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine, water and milk over rice.
Mix the soups and spoon over rice.
Lay pieces of chicken on rice and sprinkle with soup mix. Seal well with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not peek during cooking time.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: Bring water, butter, corn, carrots, onion and pepper to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in soup, then milk, Cheddar and Provolone cheese and broccoli.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts and serving temperature is reached.
Do not boil.
Garnish with broccoli flowerets, if desired.
Makes 7 to 8 cups.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Marinate chicken for 4 hours.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup Coca-Cola; add jello and stir well.
Add remaining Coke and strawberry juice.
Chill in refrigerator until almost set.
Add drained pineapple and strawberries.
Add cheese and pecans and stir until mixed.
Chill in mold.

title: scalloped ham
directions: Dice potatoes and cheese, and cut ham and pimentos in small pieces. Mix.
Place in baking dish. Pour over ingredients 1 cup of cream.
Bake 1/2 hour in moderate oven.

title: grandma sellati's lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
In Dutch oven, combine puree, paste, sugar, 1 bay leaf, dash of salt, onion, garlic, pepper and oregano to taste. Add water and heat to reach desired consistency.
Add browned meat.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: easy turkey stroganoff
directions: Combine onion, milk, beef, oatmeal, salt, pepper, garlic powder and 1 egg; mix well.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Fry in a 10-inch skillet until brown on all sides.
Place in a 10-inch casserole dish.
Spoon soup and Worcestershire sauce over meatballs.
Bake, covered with foil, for 35 minutes at 350°. Stir and baste twice.
Uncover; blend in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well and bake 10 minutes, then turn oven to 375° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: seba j. jones' easy pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add flour a small amount at a time, beat after each addition.
Add vanilla, butter, almond and sherry.
Spray pan (I use Bakers Joy).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs, milk, creamed corn and bacon drippings. Fry hamburger and onion.
Grease a large black skillet and dust with corn meal, then brown.
Then layer 1/2 batter, the Mexican cheese, hamburger and rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows on top of cake.
Return to oven until marshmallows melt.

title: apple crisp 2(diabetic)
directions: Place apple slices in small baking dish.
Sprinkle with orange juice, sugar replacement and crushed cornflakes.
Top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ranch style stew
directions: Pour over browned meat and simmer for 2 hours.
Add 6 small carrots, sliced and 3 or 4 potatoes, cubed.
Continue cooking until carrots and potatoes are done.
Make a small amount of flour and water paste and thicken juice to desired consistency.

title: sand tarts cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add well beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add vanilla.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick. Sprinkle with sugar (colored if desired).
Cut in any shape desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: In a blender, or with mixer, combine all ingredients until smooth.

title: beef 'n' broccoli stir-fry(weight watchers)
directions: In 10-inch skillet or a wok heat oil; add broccoli, carrots and onion and cook, stirring quickly and frequently, until vegetables are tender-crisp and onions are browned.
Stir in beef strips.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients, stirring to dissolve cornstarch; add to beef mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: white cheddar apple pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Top pie with 3 tablespoons brown sugar and almonds. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: scalloped broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli and onion in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cook, covered, on High, for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Drain and set vegetables aside.
Place margarine in same bowl.
Cook uncovered at High for 30 seconds.

title: chicken in egg and lemon sauce
directions: In a large metal pan, heat the oil and brown the chicken on all sides.
Add onion.
Cook until the onion is wilted.
Add broth, artichokes, salt, pepper, thyme and 1 tablespoon of the parsley.
Cook for 30 minutes slowly over low heat.
Stir in mushrooms and cook 15 minutes more or until done.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Refrigerate for 24 hours, then bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: beef and barley stew
directions: In 5-quart pot, add onions and garlic; heat 3 minutes.
Add beef and cook (medium) for 5 minutes.
Add beef broth, water, wine, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook 1 hour on medium.
Stir in barley. Cover and cook 35 minutes.
Add peas and carrots, mushrooms and pearl onions.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.

title: mock chicken parmesan
directions: Mix egg with garlic powder.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and cover with chicken crumbs.
Fry in oil until browned or crispy. Place crispy chicken in baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (cheese should completely cover the sauce in order to form a covering over the chicken).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and syrup.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add alternately with the buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, Hershey bars and pecans.
Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: company pie
directions: Mix raisins, nuts and vinegar and set aside.
Combine margarine, sugar and eggs and beat until thick.
Beat in spices and salt.
Stir in raisin mixture and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tsukemono(japanese pickle)
directions: Boil the water, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Cut cabbage in 1/8-inch pieces.
Pour boiled vinegar on cabbage. Cover with foil. Ready in 2 days.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: In large bowl, put 2 cans of soup, sour cream, chiles, green onion and olives. Mix well. Store in grated Jack cheese. Remove 2 cans of mixture and set aside. Add chicken pieces to rest of mixture. Put 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on tortilla and roll up. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Spray with cooking spray first. Pour the 2 reserved soup cans mixture over top of tortillas. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake uncovered until hot and bubbly at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: brisket roast
directions: Sprinkle beef with seasoned salt and black pepper.
Marinate overnight in salad dressing and liquid smoke.
Leave marinade in pan when ready to cook and add Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with foil and cook 4 hours at 275°.
Remove foil and pour Heinz 57 sauce over beef.
Bake an additional hour, uncovered.
Slice across the grain and enjoy.

title: fabulous fantastic fudge
directions: In a large bowl, mix chopped Hershey, chocolate chips and Fluff and set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk and bring to the boil.
Boil for 4 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over Hershey mixture and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture onto buttered cookie sheet (or spray with Pam).
Refrigerate and cut when set.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Slice bread into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Spread softened butter over 1 side of each bread slice.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cut slices into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until crisp and dry.
Yields 4 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Make into small balls, roll one side in sugar and place on cookie sheets.
Press into shape with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well and process in ice cream freezer.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a 4-quart stock pot or saucepan about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole and bake in 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings, enough for 10 to 12 pound turkey.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef.
Chop tomato, avocado, cucumber and onion. Mix all together and enjoy.

title: sweet and sour string beans
directions: Cook the string beans and drain, saving 1/4 cup of the liquid. Combine the remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and add to the cooked beans.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Beat first 7 ingredients 2 minutes; pour into pie pan.
Arrange peaches on batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and peach juice; beat on high until smooth.
Arrange cheese on peaches, about 1-inch from edge of pie plate.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: great grandmother's lightning cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan. Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Measure oil in a cup measure.
Add eggs and fill cup with milk.
Mix well and put in preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well and add chips.
Drop teaspoon size balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese squares
directions: Put 1 crescent roll package in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Whip the next three ingredients together and pour on rolls.
Place last package crescent rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done, drizzle with confectioners sugar frosting.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: "no liquid" banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Mix flour with salt and soda.
Add flour mixture slowly, beating well.
Add bananas and nuts, mixing well for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch layer pans before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: In boiling water, add onion and grits.
Cook for 30 minutes. In a separate pan, melt together butter, garlic and cheese.
To this, add
eggs and enough milk to make one cup of liquid.
Stir the liquid briskly into the grits; pour the grits into a buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes or so at 350°.
The end product will make you warble like a fat canary!

title: jackie's mexi dip(quick and easy - great for parties)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, drain.
Mix refried beans and salsa.
Place 1/2 of the hamburger on bottom of oven safe dish. Spread 1/2 of the bean-salsa mixture over beef.
Sprinkle 1/2 of scallions over beans.
Spread 8 ounces cheese over scallions. Repeat layers.
Spread sour cream over top.
Spread tomatoes around outside of dish.
Spread olives next to tomatoes.
Use remaining scallions and place in center of dish.
Cover and heat for 30 minutes.
This mixture can also be used in burrito shells.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together; add the sugar, then the egg, well beaten.
Then add the milk and lastly, the nuts, rolled in flour.
Give it 20 minutes to rise, then bake in a moderate oven, 350°, until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: snicker's cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour 1/2 cake batter in pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Melt caramels, oleo and milk in microwave.
Pour mixture over cake and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 250 degrees for 20 minutes, then 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes until firm to touch.

title: mm's herb bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add spices and mix.
Cut bread clear through and dip in herb butter.
Wrap reassembled loaf in heavy-duty foil and bake at 350° until crisp, about 20 minutes.
If bread is not crispy enough open foil to expose top of bread and cook additional 10 minutes or so.

title: july 4th cake
directions: Cut cake into 3 layers.
Place bottom layer on plate and coat with pie filling.
Then a layer of Cool Whip.
Add second cake layer.
Place a layer of strawberries, then a layer of Cool Whip. Top with last cake layer.
Ice the whole cake with Cool Whip.
Let set 3 or 4 hours.
Garnish the top with blueberry pie filling in the center and strawberries on the edges.
Must keep in refrigerator.
Makes a big cake.
It is pretty and very good.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Place 1/2 cup of dry mixture into a cup.
Fill with boiling water.

title: lemon relish
directions: Trim rind from two lemons and cut into fine strips.
Cover with boiling water in a small bowl.
Drain, reserving lemon water. Cut peel and white membrane from all lemons and cut them into thin slices, removing all seeds.
Place slices in a glass bowl. Mix sage, sugar and one cup reserved lemon water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 4 minutes or until thick.
Add reserved lemon strips to the pan and pour the sauce over the lemon slices.
Cover and chill.
Good with fowl or pork.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: round steak
directions: Combine flour and next 4 ingredients together.
Flour meat and brown in frypan in 1/4 cup oil.
Remove from pan and add to drippings the remaining flour mixture.
Thicken drippings and then add water, bouillon and sauce to drippings.
Put meat back in pan and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and salt in large skillet. Drain excess fat. Add spaghetti sauce. Cook until mixture is thick enough to hold shape.
Cool.
Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine vegetables and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients. Boil for 1 minute and cool.
Pour over chopped vegetables and mix well. Place in containers and freeze.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together (set aside). Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flavor to milk; alternate milk and flour.
Let flour end last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press out cans of rolls and press the edges together on a rectangle cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on the can; cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and salad dressing mix.
Spread over cooled rolls.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top of vegetables.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Chill, then cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice 15 minutes.
Put in baking dish.
Add chicken. Sprinkle celery on top, then mix soup, broth, mayonnaise and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shortbread shortcake
directions: In mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Mix in flour and chocolate.
Form dough into two balls (one slightly larger than the other). On a floured surface, roll balls into 7-inch circles (one thicker than the other).
Transfer to greased baking sheets. Prick all over with fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or just until golden.
Allow to cool 5 minutes; cut thinner circle into 8 equal wedges.
Cool on racks.
To assemble, place circle on a serving plate.
Top with cream and strawberries.
Set wedges into the cream at an angle, points toward center.
Cut into wedges.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie shell with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; cool.

title: honeyed zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise and slice into 2 to 3-inch pieces. Saute lightly in butter. Add honey and tomatoes and bring to a boil. Cook 5 minutes longer. (Can add a cup of bread
crumbs with tomatoes, if desired.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Sift meal, salt and soda.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, oil and corn; mix well.
Pour half of this in pan, then put meat over this, then put grated cheese and cover with other half of mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary's cheese strata
directions: Layer bread cubes and grated cheese in a greased pan.
Mix in a separate bowl the remaining ingredients and then pour over layered mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and enjoy!

title: stoby's cheese dip
directions: Boil water and add Coffee-mate and cheese.
Stir until melted. Make a paste of flour and butter.
Add spices to paste.
Add paste to cheese mixture.
Add picante sauce and chili.
Heat until well blended.

title: triffle
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Spread in layers:
1/2 cake, broken into crumbs, 1/2 of Kahlua, 1/2 of chocolate pudding, 8 ounces of Cool Whip and 1/2 of crushed candy.
Repeat layering.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: irish potato pie
directions: Mix hot potatoes, sugar, butter and milk.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: lime pear salad
directions: Heat pear juice and mix with the lime jello; let thicken slightly.
Cream the softened cream cheese and mash the pears. Add both to jello mixture and mix in Cool Whip.
Beat together until blended.

title: uncle ben's sheet cake
directions: Sift together the first 2 ingredients
in a large bowl. In saucepan bring to a boil the
next
ingredients and pour over dry ingredients.
Stir
in
the
remaining
ingredients. Bake at 400° in a greased and floured
sheet
pan
for 20 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Combine contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, stuffing mix, and water; set aside.
Place chicken in 13x9 inch baking dish or 2 qt. casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream, then pour over chicken.
Spoon stuffing mixture evenly over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: citrus shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
For sauce, combine next 7 ingredients; set aside.
Heat wok on high.
Fry broccoli in oil until crisp-tender; remove.
Fry shrimp 1/2 at a time until pink. Return all shrimp and veggies to wok; push to sides.
Pour sauce in center of wok; stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir all and cook 2 more minutes.
Serve with or over rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in mold or Pyrex dish.
Chill.

title: tea
directions: Heat 1 quart water and tea bags just until water starts to boil. Remove from heat and cover. Let set for about 30 minutes. Remove tea bags and pour into a gallon pitcher. Add sugar to suit your taste. Finish filling pitcher with water.

title: "tastees"
directions: Add beef and water to kettle.
Mix condiments in cup and add to meat.
Add onion, salt and pepper and Accent.
Stir constantly on medium heat and brown.
Cook on low heat, simmering in flavor. Drain juice before serving on buns.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook until thickened.
Pour over cheese and pimentos while hot.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; cut shortening into mixture.
Add buttermilk to make a soft dough. Pour dough onto a floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in baking pan and bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; let cool.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and ginger ale.
Mix well and add frozen fruits.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix ingredients until fluffy.
Pour into crust.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
Contains 43 calories per serving.

title: banana christmas bread
directions: In a bowl, cream together the sugar and butter. Blend in beaten eggs. Add mashed bananas.
Mix in flour and soda.
Stir well.
Blend in nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Pour into a large greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until tests done.

title: chocolate-chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown meat in butter or margarine.
Stir in other ingredients. Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma hall's potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cook in water in a large pot.
When potatoes are tender, add milk; do not boil milk.
