In a small bowl mix flour, salt and egg until crumbly.
Add to potatoes and milk. Stir constantly.
Add celery seed and pepper.
Soup may thicken. You can add water or milk for thickness you like.
Serve warm.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: On a piece of wax paper combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumb mixture to coat.
Place in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish. Bake near center of 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Add apple juice, green onion and parsley to remaining melted butter (about 1/2 cup).
When chicken in golden brown pour butter sauce mixture around and over it.
Return to oven for 5 minutes more or just until sauce is hot.
Serve with sauce spooned over chicken.
Serves 2.

title: coleslaw
directions: Grate or finely chop all vegetables.
In a separate bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until blended. Pour mayonnaise mixture over the vegetables and stir to combine. Mixture will seem "thick;"
it becomes more liquid as it chills. Chill well before serving.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with combined crumbs, cheese, parsley, chives and seasonings.
Place in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, stir together 2 cups of flour and the yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, shortening, sugar and salt until scalded.
Add mashed potatoes if cold, also eggs if cold.
All ingredients have to be warm.
Add to dry mixture in bowl.
Beat at slow speed for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or up to one week.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble
and
saute sausage, drain and set aside.
Beat eggs, add
milk,	salt, pepper and mustard.
Arrange the bread crumbs across the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish. Top with sausage, sprinkle with cheese and pour eggs over the top. Refrigerate
overnight.
Bake
at
for
to
60 minutes. Serves 10.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Place cake mix in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Mix on low to blend.
Beat on high for 4 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and flour. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Spread cherry filling (or your favorite filling) on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar frosting (powdered sugar and milk) on top.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients together, except cheese.
Place in baking dish.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: marinated olives
directions: Place all ingredients into a covered bowl; shake to coat olives with the marinade.
Leave at room temperature for at least 2 hours.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes enough zucchini to make a gallon.
Let stand in 1 gallon water with 1 cup lime added for 24 hours.
Rinse four to five times.
Mix sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Pour over rinsed zucchini and let stand 24 hours.
Then add food coloring and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: old fashion cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and shortening.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lobster cheesecake
directions: Note:
All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: caribbean island sausage and rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water or juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil in large saucepan and stir in rice, 1 tablespoon of the butter and salt.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces. Combine all ingredients. Use just enough mayonnaise to bind ingredients together.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in sugar, then crumbs (reserving 1/3 cup for garnish).
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Cool.
In large bowl, mix sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in pie filling and fruit cocktail.
Pour over crust. Top with whipped topping and crumbs.
Freeze 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before cutting.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices.

title: chocolate-coconut pinwheels
directions: Stir together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt. In a large mixer bowl beat shortening and butter until butter is softened.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours or until easy to handle.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 greased (16 ounce) tin cans.
(Interior of tin cans should be gold looking not silver.)
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: onion steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown in large skillet. Mix water and onion soup.
Pour over steak.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add mushroom soup and stir.
Cover.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Serve with soup gravy over noodles, potatoes or rice.

title: orange-raisin cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening well.
Stir in beaten egg.
Add alternately the flour and the sour milk into which soda has been mixed, with the flour.
Grind oranges, rind and all, with raisins. Set aside 3 tablespoons and add the remaining to cake batter.
Bake in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch square pan for 35 to 40 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.
Add confectioners sugar to the 3 tablespoons orange and raisin mixture.
Mix and pour over cake while it is still very hot.
It makes a delicious frosting.
The mixture may be added to 7-Minute Frosting if the cake is baked in layers.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and powder, salt and cocoa.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add food coloring; mix well.
Add the buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake 24 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese coconut frosting.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain.
Combine onion and green pepper in a large bowl.
Cover.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over veggies in bowl.
Cover and marinate in fridge for several hours or overnight.

title: harriett's southern biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in Crisco with fork until coarse and grainy, then stir in buttermilk.
Knead a few times. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Heat remaining Crisco in a cast-iron skillet in the oven at 400°.
Place biscuits in skillet.
Cook in oven until light brown.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put cheese slices on chicken.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing.
Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until very light brown (crust will be soft).
Remove from oven; immediately place separated squares of chocolate candy on crust.
Let chocolate soften, then spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
While warm, cut into bars, 2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: polly's hoagies
directions: Cut bread horizontally into halves; spread bottom half with butter.
Layer cheese, salami, lettuce, tomatoes, onion, ham, turkey breast and green pepper; put hot pepper on top with remaining half of bread.
Secure loaf with 6 long wooden picks or small skewers.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine all but the last 3 ingredients; mix well, then stuff into seeded and split peppers.
Arrange in baking dish; pour oil over them.

title: jello cake
directions: First, bake cake in a sheet cake pan, then fix Jell-O as directed on the box.
Poke holes in the cake after it cools.
Pour Jell-O over cake, then fix pudding as directed on the back of the box.
Pour over the cake, then add the whipped cream over the top of the cake.
Set in refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add bones and V-8 juice.
Add 3 large glasses of water.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cook for about 2 hours.
Add cabbage, corn and frozen mixed vegetables. Cook for about another hour or hour and 1/2.
Add seasoning to taste.

title: ratatouille
directions: Wash, peel and slice vegetables into 1/4-inch slices. Cut green peppers in strips. Toss together. In Dutch oven, heat oil. Add onions and pepper; cook 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients. Cook 25 to 30 minutes until tender and excess water is cooked away. Serves 8 to 10. Serve hot or cold.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: To make stuffing, saute bacon with onions; mix in bread cubes, parsley, celery salt and pepper.
Spread each portion of steak with stuffing and roll up.
Hold together with toothpicks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Roll in pecans and/or mix pecans into cheese ball mixture.
Serve with Sociables or your favorite snack crackers.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Brown sliced sausage with onion over low heat.
Add beans and tomatoes, undrained.
Season with garlic and Italian spices. Simmer until mixture thickens and flavors blend, about 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and mix juice with soup. Layer asparagus, cheese, sliced eggs, crackers and soup in a casserole dish. Top with butter soaked crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three layer pie
directions: Melt margarine and add flour and nuts.
Mix and press in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: russian chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with foil.
Arrange chicken evenly in dish; salt and pepper to taste.
Place sliced onion on top of chicken.
Mix Russian dressing and preserves together. Pour over chicken.
May mix a small amount of water with dressing mixture if it appears too thick.
Seal with a second piece of foil.
Bake at 350° until chicken juices are clear.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni 10 minutes.
Mix soup, milk, peas and tuna in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Stir in macaroni.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbling.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: memorial auxiliary punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl and add ice.

title: jelly doughnuts
directions: Scald milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 1 cup of cold water, yeast cake, nutmeg and well beaten egg(s).
Flour as needed for kneading.
After dough has been properly kneaded, put in warm place to rise for about 45 minutes.
Roll out and let rise again after cutting with cookie cutter.
Fry as any other doughnut. Slit open.
Fill with jelly.
Close them up.
Serve fresh.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: quiche
directions: Combine egg, flour, Parmesan cheese, 1/2 cup milk and seasonings.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in remaining milk; stir in half of Swiss cheese.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 23 g, protein 14 g, fat 11 g, calories 247.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fruit exchange.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, mix with egg and onion and stir in flour.
Form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: fruit crumble
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, oil and cinnamon.
Mix until crumbly.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch square baking pan with half the mixture, pressing firmly.
Add sliced fruit of your choice.
Boil juice, sugar and cornstarch until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour over fruit and cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
In another bowl, beat egg, vinegar, sugar and water.
Add to flour.
Makes 7 crusts.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cut crust off bread and cut into squares.
Grate cheese. Layer the bread squares and cheese, starting with bread and finishing with cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, dry mustard, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over bread and cheese.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then let cool for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Dissolve sugars in cream and boil to 228°, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook until mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
Cool until barely warm.
Beat until thickened, but still glossy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. The drops will flatten into patties.
Makes 12 pralines.

title: supreme zucchini dish
directions: Peel and dice zucchini.
Boil for 5 minutes in salt water. Drain.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
In the meantime, combine and mix together tomatoes, sugar, salt, oregano and flour.
Add this to onion mixture and cook until thickened. Grease casserole.
Put zucchini in, then pour tomato mixture over. Put grated cheese over tomatoes, then top with bread crumbs.
Put small dots of butter on top of bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(Cover with tinfoil the first 20 to 25 minutes, then unwrap for remaining baking period.)

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter or margarine, chocolate and peanut butter in microwave or double boiler.
Mix well and pour over Rice Chex. Make sure Chex is covered good with chocolate.
Pour chocolate covered Chex into clean bag (trash or grocery) and dump whole box of powdered sugar in.
Shake well after making sure bag is closed. Enjoy!

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until
light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured jumbo, fluted mold pan (12 cup Bundt pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours until cake tester comes out clean.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed (5 minutes).
Gradually add granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin; add lemon juice.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add all ingredients to grits.
Combine all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Great served with pinto beans or barbecue brisket or ribs.

title: fresh vegetable and tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed; drain and rinse with cool water. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
Garnish with red and green pepper rings.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve cold.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Grate carrot and potatoes.
Measure and set aside.
Cream butter; add sugar and blend well.
Add carrot and 1/2 potatoes and mix well.
Sprinkle fruits with flour and add to first mixture. Add flour and spices, which have been sifted together.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/2 cup of potatoes and add it last.
Mix lightly together.
Pour into buttered bowls.
Tie down and steam for 3 hours.
(I double this recipe.)
This pudding is good with caramel sauce over it.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, Karo and water until clear.
Blend in Jell-O.
Cool filling.
Place fresh strawberries in crust.
Pour mixture over or stir berries into filling and then pour into crust.
Chill several hours until set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: jello dessert
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions on package. Chill in refrigerator.
Beat with mixer until foamy consistency.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until partially set.
Remove and add fruit cocktail.
Mix in.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: fruited chicken salad(finger sandwiches)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This will make 32 (2-inch) square sandwiches.
Spread salad mixture on buttered bread.

title: tomato cheese dip
directions: Puree can of tomatoes.
Pour into double boiler to heat.
Cut cheese into small chunks and add to the tomato puree.
When cheese is melted, let cool and put in tight container.
Refrigerate.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Heat until well blended.
Stir in apples, coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Pour topping over hot cake.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: To make sauce:
Mash garlic with salt.
Combine with onion and olive oil in heavy skillet and saute until transparent.
Add tomato sauce and cumin.
Bring to slow boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour (best done a day ahead).
Cut cheese into pieces 1/2 inch thick and 1 inch wide.
Wrap chilies around cheese.
Heat oil to 350°.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Stir into a paste.
Add chicken stock and liquid from the canned items.
Add salt, pepper and herbs.
If mixture is too thick, add water.
If too thin, add instant mashed potatoes.
Just before serving, add the asparagus, pimentos, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
This recipe can be stretched with instant potatoes and water.

title: chicken and green bean stir-fry with black beans
directions: Marinate the chicken with the ingredients and let sit at least 1 hour.
Prepare the sauce.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and chill 8 hours.
Stir in 1 cup vodka just before serving.
Serve over ice.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: old fashioned waffles
directions: Beat flour and milk.
Add margarine and beat.
Add well beaten egg yolks and beat again.
Add baking powder and pinch of salt. Beat very hard for a few minutes.
Fold in well beaten egg whites. Have waffle iron very hot.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper; coat meat cubes. Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup, 2 1/2 cups water, onion and basil.

title: party punch base
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Strain out spices and chill.
Combine with juices.
Add 7-Up or Squirt.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake crust 10 minutes.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in sugar and butter.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with ice cream.

title: alsatina potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in kettle with cold water; bring to boil.
Cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Peel potatoes. When cool enough to handle, cut into 1/4-inch slices and put in mixing bowl.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Chop coarsely and set aside.
Add onion, parsley, salt and pepper to taste to potatoes.
Add vinegar, oil and 1/2 bacon, then toss mixture.
Spoon into salad bowl; garnish with remaining bacon and lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Put in liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Add raisins and apples.
Mix well.
Place in muffin pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Place all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover and cook for 3 minutes.
Uncover and continue to cook, leaving spoon in.
Cook until candy thermometer reaches 300°. Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Break into serving pieces when cold.

title: nachos
directions: Check to see that the oven racks are in the middle of the oven. Then preheat the oven to 400°.
Spread the tortilla chips on a cookie sheet.
Cover the chips with the grated cheese.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes, or until the cheese melts.
Be sure to use a potholder to take the cookie sheet out of the oven.
To make it spicy, put a little taco sauce on each nacho as you eat it.

title: lo-cal cheesecake
directions: Whip cream and set aside.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool. Blend with cream cheese in blender.
Add vanilla, rinds, lemon juice and sugar.
Fold all into whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: baked sea scallops
directions: Divide scallops into 4 ovenproof dishes or 1 (9-inch) pie plate.
Add lemon juice.
Place crackers on top of scallops. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and brown on top.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients and make into small meatballs.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Combine the remaining ingredients and heat until dissolved.
Pour over meatballs and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(May be frozen.)

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Roll dough into forty 1-inch balls.
Place balls in small muffin tins; bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Immediately after removing from oven, press peanut butter cups into center of each cookie until only top of peanut butter cup shows.
Leave in tins 10 minutes and then remove.

title: easy punch
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water. In a separate container, mix strawberry Kool-Aid with sugar and 2 gallons water. Combine the Jell-O mixture with this mixture and then add 4 cans of pineapple juice. Stir all ingredients together and pour into gallon containers to refrigerate. Makes 4 gallons of punch.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In a bowl, mix soup, onion and water chestnuts.
In a 1 1/2-quart round Pyrex casserole dish, layer beans and soup mixture, sprinkling garlic salt and pepper after each soup layer. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Add layer of onion rings and bake 10 minutes more.

title: russian tea
directions: While tea is simmering, put in lemon, cinnamon and cloves. Strain and add juices.
Sweeten to taste.

title: mother's strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and flour.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Add Jell-O and oil to cake mixture, add eggs, one at a time, and the strawberries and juice.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol's zucchini relish
directions: Combine in kettle: water, vinegar and salt.
Heat to boiling. Pour over beans and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Will be ready for eating in 2 weeks.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Slightly break Ramen noodles and put in bowl.
Pour oil and vinegar mixture over noodles; let sit no longer than 2 hours.
Mix rest of ingredients together (chicken is optional).
Add noodles and dressing.
Serve.

title: noodle and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Drain.
Melt margarine.
Mix ingredients.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creme de menthe brownies no. 1
directions: Beat it for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and cool, then refrigerate until really cool, about 1/2 hour.

title: butter fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and add sugar; mix well.
Add this mixture to the margarine and flour and mix well.
Add chopped fruits, nuts and raisins; mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
(If tube pan is not available, use loaf pan.)
Bake at 275° for about 2 hours. Invert pan to cool.
To remove, run spatula around edges, including tube.

title: crawfish au gratin
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and seasoning.
Add cream. Stir in cheese into hot mixture until melted.
Add crawfish and cook 10 minutes on low heat.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until bubbly.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Serve in French bread loaf which has been scooped out. Slice the bread that you scoop out to eat with the dip.

title: chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions in Dutch oven or large roasting pan until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, reserved liquid, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes, or until desired consistency.
Makes 24 servings (1 1/3 cups each).

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash the avocados with a fork and add the seasonings to taste. Squeeze the lemons over the avocados.
Mix everything.
Use Doritos to dip.

title: macaroni-beef casserole(serves 6)
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain fat.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top last 10 minutes, if desired.

title: green chili casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and ground beef.
Drain mixture.

title: brunch at the martin's
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Place hash browns in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer sausage, cheese and green pepper.
Combine eggs and milk, stirring well.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tangie island pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add one egg at a time.
Add lemon and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour and baking powder.
Add this mix to the first mixture alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: carolyn's cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll in pecan pieces, forming a ball.
Best if set overnight.

title: fudgy granola clusters
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, microwave chocolate chips on Medium setting (50%) for 2 minutes.
Stir chocolate; microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop generous measuring teaspoonfuls of mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until set, about 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen Clusters.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in a casserole dish.
Cover with, in order, a layer of flour, then sugar, then grated cheese, then crushed crackers.
Pour melted margarine over the layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: colorado biscuits
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together into a bowl.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Stir milk and egg into flour-shortening mixture.
Roll and cut.
Don't roll too thin. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen biscuits.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Put ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add vegetables and soup mixed together.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix vegetables. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate, covered, at least 2 hours.
Keeps up to 3 weeks.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water; leave 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; cool.
Add beaten eggs and yeast. Add flour, a cup at a time; blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick fluffy frosting
directions: Pour milk into a deep narrow bowl; add whipped topping mix and pudding mix.
Beat until well-blended, using low speed. Gradually increase beating speed to high and whip until mixture forms soft peaks, 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes enough to frost 2 layer 9-inch cake.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: spiced orange tea mix
directions: Stir together drink and tea powder, sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Cover and store for up to 4 months in an airtight container in a cool dry place.
Stir before using.
Makes 2 cups (enough for 12 servings).

title: german chocolate caramel deluxe cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over it.
Put caramel topping on top of that.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Crumble candy bars on top of that.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix milk and egg in bowl.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls into oil.
Fry until deep golden brown, turning once.
Heat oil to 375°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine and pour over spareribs.
Cook for 2 hours at 350°. Remove ribs and thicken sauce for gravy, if desired.

title: venus soup
directions: Saute hamburger and onion.
Add remainder of ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: jeweled fruitcake
directions: Combine flour and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl, stir well.
Add pecans and remaining ingredients, stir well.
Spoon batter into prepared pan sprayed with cooking (Pam) oil.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Shield cake the last 30 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove cake from pan.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Wrap cake and store in refrigerator.
Yields 24 servings (153 calories per 1/2 inch slice).

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, ground black, cayenne pepper and crushed red pepper.
Drain if necessary.
Put mixture into a 5-quart slow cooker (crock-pot) and add the V-8 juice, chili powder and chili beans.
Cook 12 to 14 hours on low heat, stirring every few hours.
About 1 hour before serving, add additional hot pepper powder to tate.

title: asparagus stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry asparagus and pepper in oil over high heat until almost tender, approximately 8 minutes.
Add shrimp and soy sauce. Stir until shrimp turns pink.
Add garlic, zest of lemon, ginger, salt and pepper flakes.
Cook until hot, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with scallion and coriander over the top.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix well the egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch and cold water and cook until thick.
Then add lemon juice, margarine and salt. Cover and let cool.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baked pie shell. Top with meringue if desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together to taste.
The taste should be slightly tart.
Half mixture and add 2 bottles of ginger ale to punch bowl.
Add sherbet of color and flavor to punch bowl mixture.
Use other half of mixture and ginger ale and sherbet as needed.

title: pudding frosting
directions: To baked, hot cake, poke holes through cake.
Combine pudding with sugar.
Stir in milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Do not overblend. Before pudding thickens, pour 1/2 of thin pudding evenly over warm cake into holes.
Allow pudding to thicken slightly.
Pour remaining 1/2 over cake.
Cover and chill for 1 hour before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: coconut tarts
directions: Mix all together.
Place one heaping tablespoon of dough in ungreased muffin cup or one heaping teaspoon in miniature muffin cup.
Press and shape to form pastry shell.
Makes 24 large or 48 small tarts.

title: grape parfait
directions: Boil grapes in brandy for 4 or 5 minutes.
Put ice cream in serving bowls and pour grape mixture over.
Serves 8.

title: creamy macaroni salad(fat-free)
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Add all ingredients and toss to coat. Cover and chill.

title: ham loaf
directions: No salt is needed.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Place banana into blender and add sugar or sweetener.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in 1/2 cup cold water; add ice, vanilla and dry milk.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into chilled glasses.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix.
Blend well; stir in sour cream. Chill thoroughly and use as a dip with fresh fruit.
Yields 3 cups.

title: shrimp cakes
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until soft.
Stir in flour, mustard, cream, salt and pepper. Stir until mixture is smooth and begins to thicken.
Add shrimp and mix well.
Put in a bowl; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. After chilling, form into patties about 2 to 3 inches in diameter. Dip into beaten egg and then into cracker crumbs.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet until sizzling.
Fry patties until crispy on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken and crabmeat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then layer fresh mushrooms, soup and Swiss cheese. Cover with dry stuffing mix (and seasonings).
Pour 1 cup butter over all.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: baked tenderloin
directions: Put tenderloin in cake pan.
Tuck under ends.
Pepper entire surface.
Sprinkle garlic powder over all.
Cube up butter and place on top.
Sprinkle lots of soy sauce on top.
Bake in a 500° oven for 30 minutes.
Test and keep on until desired doneness. Baste often.
If liquid bakes dry, add water.

title: orange supreme
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let congeal firm.
Add other ingredients.
Then fold in 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Then refrigerate.

title: sauteed chicken strips over fettuccine with cheese and cream
directions: Cut chicken breast halves into strips about 3/4 to 1-inch wide.
Saute until lightly browned in olive oil and minced garlic. Remove from skillet, drain on paper towel and place in covered pan in slightly warm oven to maintain heat.
Cook fettuccine as directed on package.
Meanwhile, heat margarine and whipping cream in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until margarine is melted.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Drain fettuccine.
Pour sauce over fettuccine; toss.
Place serving of fettuccine on plate.
Place slivers of sauteed chicken breasts decoratively atop fettuccine and sprinkle with parsley.

title: mexican tomato sauce(yields about 7 quarts)
directions: Caution:
Wear rubber
gloves
while handling chiles or wash hands thoroughly with soap and water before touching your face.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well. Spread mixture on 8-inch tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down; cover and chill 4 hours or longer. Slice into 1/2 to 1-inch pinwheels.
Serve with salsa on the side. May also add 2 cups diced chicken or ham.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Arrange breasts on baking dish.
Pour sour cream and soup mix over all.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 8 people.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix and dry pudding mix. Add oil and Mountain Dew.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat about 4 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan about 30 to 35 minutes.
Add topping while hot.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You may top with the following sauce, but it's good without it.

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in scalded milk.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Add small amount of mixture to egg yolks.
Stir into remaining mixture. Cook until thick.
Add butter.
Top with meringue.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and peppers until onions are clear.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly about 3 hours.

title: karo icebox christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Beat oleo until soft and creamy. Add Karo and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands until stiff dough is formed.
Shape into 3 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Reserve 3/4 cup cake mix for second layer.
Set aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Form bite size balls.
Bring jelly and chili sauce to boil.
Put meatballs in sauce and reduce heat. Simmer 2 hours.
Stir gently with wooden spoon.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Mix together.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer in order 1/2 of the following: noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: glazed carrots and parsnips
directions: Cook carrots and parsnips in a small amount of boiling water and salt for 10 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
Combine orange juice, honey, lime juice, lime rind and ginger root in small saucepan over medium heat about 5 minutes or until heated.
Pour orange juice mixture over carrot mixture and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: maryland collard greens
directions: Combine water and ham hock in a large pot, boil for about 1 hour.
Cut greens into 1/2-inch strips and wash thoroughly.
Scald greens for 5 minutes in a pot of boiling water; drain the greens. Mix the greens, salt, pepper and red pepper with the ham hock. Cook 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° to 400°, until light brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Remove tips and disjoint.
Dredge in flour and fry in vegetable oil.
Combine other ingredients into a sauce.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: sweet 'n' sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and drain off grease.
For best results, use a cast-iron or other heavy skillet.
Mix pineapple juice, water, bouillon cube, cranberry sauce, brown sugar and vinegar.
Pour over pork chops and simmer 40 minutes.
Add pineapple slices and green pepper rings and simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove pork chops, pineapple and pepper slices.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch.
Pour gravy over chops; serve with rice.

title: kim's double chocolate "sugar-free" pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In blender, crush cookies. Melt margarine and pour over crumbs. Add nuts and mix well. Press into pie plate, covering bottom and sides. Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl; set aside.
Place butter, salad oil, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Pour over sugar and flour and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Pour into 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mam's delicious peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare flaky pie crust or store-bought pie shell.
Melt butter or margarine.
Cool and set aside.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl and stir.
Add eggs and shortening and stir.
Now gradually add buttermilk until you have a firm but not stiff dough (like a biscuit dough).
Put on lightly floured board and knead about 2 minutes until dough is smooth.
Flatten dough and put in a well-greased 9-inch layer cake pan.
Cut a 4-inch cross in the center.
Bake in oven set at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with cut up chicken.
Mix the soup with the sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush the Ritz crackers and pour on 1 stick melted margarine.
Sprinkle on the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Drain and chop olives, pimientos and sweet peppers.
Mix in with cream cheese and chill. Spread on your favorite snack crackers or veggies, etc.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain. Add onion and peppers. cook until tender; drain. Place all ingredients in crockpot and cook on low for 6-8 hours.

title: baked summer vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into large dice. Cut corn from cobs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in about 20 ounces of water until done.
(Do not let water boil away.)
Cool.
Remove from bone in small pieces. Set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring stock to boil with water; add chicken cut into chunks, simmer 10 minutes, remove chicken.
Add potatoes, simmer 10 minutes; remove.
Add carrots, simmer 15 minutes; remove.
Add broccoli, simmer 3 minutes; remove.
Boil stock mixture to 2 cups. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute 8 minutes.
Add flour; stir until golden (2 minutes).
Whisk in stock mixture. Mix in milk and thyme, cook until thick, 10 minutes.
Add chicken and veggies.
Season with salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 425°. Line 2 (9-inch) glass dishes with crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Fill crusts with filling and add top crust, brushed with egg.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk, cocoa and butter together. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and rolled oats. Mix together and drop on wax paper.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Coat chops with seasoned flour.
Insert one clove in each chop.
Heat butter in a flameproof casserole and brown chops lightly on both sides.

title: chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in nonstick spray in nonstick pan until limp.
Remove from pan.
Cook ground beef until crumbly and brown in same pan.
Drain.
Place kidney beans in colander.
Rinse with cool water.
Add rinsed beans and all other ingredients to saucepan.
Stir, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add water, if necessary.
Serve with crackers or hot tortillas.
Serves 4.
Can be frozen.
To reheat, place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: almond bark drops
directions: Melt almond bark; stir until smooth. Pour melted almond bark over mixture or stir until coated. Drop by spoonful. Cool.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice and buttered bread crumbs. Grease casserole.
Place in cooked rice.
Pour other mixture over. Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in a buttered casserole dish in order listed.
Mix eggs, mustard, milk and salt; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Falls as it stands.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tuscan bean soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large stockpot over medium heat.
Add the ham or Italian sausage (casing removed) and saute for 2 minutes.
Add the onion, celery, carrot, and garlic; saute for 2 minutes or until soft.
Add the water, beans, bay leaves and broth and bring soup to a boil.
Partially cover, reduce heat and simmer soup for 20 minutes.
Add the parsley, sherry, and black pepper; cook 1 minute. Discard bay leaves. 4 servings (1 1/2 c. each).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in small amount of shortening in heavy frying pan.
Add seasonings, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Simmer a few minutes and serve over hot cooked noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: buttermilk chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix together sugar, Crisco oil and beaten eggs.
Add to mixture, a small amount at a time, the salt, soda and cocoa. Combine to other mixture the water, buttermilk and vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread icing over hot cake and allow to cool in pan.

title: crabmeat dreams
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and refrigerate.
Toast bread rounds on one side.
When ready to serve, pile crabmeat on toast rounds.
Sprinkle with grated American cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: turkey tetrazzini(yields 6 servings)
directions: Make first 6 ingredients into a white sauce. Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of butter. Add with turkey and rice to white sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chilled avocado soup
directions: Combine avocado, onion and 1 can consomme in container of electric blender.
Cover and blend until pureed.
Pour into a mixing bowl; stir in remaining consomme and last 3 ingredients. Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat. Stir-fry vegetables 4 to 5 minutes; remove vegetables from pan. Add remaining oil to skillet.
Stir-fry chicken 4 minutes or until tender.
Return vegetables to pan with chicken; mix well.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine shortening and sugar and cream well.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Mix well. Shape into balls using a level tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Roll into crushed cornflakes and top with a 1/4 of maraschino cherry.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not stack or store until cookies are cold.

title: down east blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a glass pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix together butter, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Blend in cream and 2 cups flour.
Fold in berries.
Dust top with 1/4 cup sugar and nutmeg.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Mix white sauce and cabbage in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Add caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl stir together the mayonnaise, vinegar and pepper until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; place in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Spread Mustard Glaze over ham loaf during last half hour of baking, basting often with sauce in the pan.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Soak bread in milk; crush with hands until well mixed. Then add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins and stir well. Pour margarine in bottom of pan and bake till very firm. Let cool; then cube pudding and place in individual dessert dish. When ready, serve. Add sauce and heat under broiler. Serve with whiskey sauce.

title: cherry cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk. Add cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes.
Let potatoes soak in water for 30 minutes.
Place oil into a plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake until well coated.
Place potato wedges onto a baking sheet.
Mix Italian seasoning with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: san francisco pork chops
directions: Combine sherry, brown sugar, soy sauce and red pepper flakes; set aside.
Heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add chops and cook until browned on each side.
Pour sauce over chops; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until cooked through.
Add water (if needed) to keep sauce form reducing too much.
Remove chops.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Add buttermilk to potatoes.
Do mash potatoes, then proceed with following:
With oil, brown onions, mushrooms and pepper in large frypan until golden or soft.
Add ground sirloin; cook until medium-well, stirring frequently.
Reduce to low heat.
Add beef gravy.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Place 3 pecan halves on a buttered aluminum foil-lined cookie sheet.
Put a caramel on each group of pecans.
Put in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; flatten the caramels with a lightly buttered spoon.
Cover with melted chocolate (melt in double boiler) and place in refrigerator until hard.
These are delicious!!

title: grilled donut desserts
directions: Cut donuts and marshmallows horizontally in half.
Place donuts, cut side down, on cooking surface of grill, 5 to 6 inches from medium coals.
Place marshmallow halves, cut side down, over holes in donuts.
Cover and grill 2 to 3 minutes or until cut sides of donuts are golden brown and marshmallows are soft.
Immediately push chocolate kisses, point side down, into marshmallows.
Then enjoy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: texas fudge pie
directions: Melt together in microwave:
chocolate morsels, margarine or butter and water, then add condensed milk, eggs, vanilla and salt. Pour in a 9 or 10-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans on top of the filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: indian cornbread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter until smooth.
Add pumpkin, milk and corn meal. Beat until smooth.
With wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture, mixing until it just combines.
Don't overstir.
Gently stir in blueberries and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab bake
directions: This is a great dip for Longaberger basket parties.
Mix all ingredients well and put into Woven Traditions small mixing bowl. Put 1/2 cup or more slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve in your Longaberger Bread Basket with heated Bread Basket Brick with crisp crackers.

title: chicken neapolitan
directions: Baste the chicken with olive oil.
Brown 30 minutes at 350°. Then season the chicken and vegetables with the bay leaves, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Add wine, chicken and beef stock. Cover with water; sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and oregano. Cover pan with tin foil.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine pecans and coconut in small bowl.
Sprinkle in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix, using package directions. Pour into prepared pan.
Cream margarine and cream cheese in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sure shot rolls
directions: Mix shortening, hot water, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, add beaten egg, yeast and flour (enough to make soft dough).
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and spread with melted butter.
Cut with small cutter and fold in half and pinch together.
Place pinched edges up on greased pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: moon balls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and form balls.
In a zipper sealed bag, crush the cereal and drop balls into the crushed cereal.
Seal and shake until balls are covered, then put into an airtight container and chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Enjoy!
Serves 24.
Easy for children to do.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cook cake for 15 minutes before pouring glaze.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand while you heat milk and butter.
Cool.
Mix yeast mixture, flour and milk.
Let stand 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll 3/4-inch thick and shape as desired.
Rise until double.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Brush with butter immediately after removing from oven.
Makes 12.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain well.
Mix soup, sour cream and water and stir into beef.
Place noodles in bottom of casserole dish and pour beef-soup mixture over them.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until noodles are tender.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients with mixer.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Serve with sliced fruit for dipping.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken (reserve a little broth if needed). Cut into small pieces when cool. Mix in big bowl with mixed vegetables (liquid too) and both cans soup. Thaw pie crust to room temperature. Place one crust in bottom and up sides of 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan. Pour in mixture. Top with other crust. Bake at 350° for 30 - 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frank-potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine potatoes, vegetables, onion, parsley flakes, bouillon cubes and salt.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add franks.

title: merry cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In 3 qt bowl combine flour, butter and brown sugar.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart pan and cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter, mixing well. Add Special K, mixing until blended.
Pour mixture into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt Nestles together over low
heat, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat and spoon evenly over Special K mixture.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, water and onion soup until done.
Cok pork sausage in large skillet until brown.
Drain.
Save drippings.
Put drippings back in pan; add chopped onions, bell pepper, pimentos, mushrooms and little salt, pepper and Accent.
Saute until tender.
Put pork sausage in large bowl; add 1/2 stick oleo and mushroom soup.
Stir.
Add all the rest ingredients to sausage mix; stir all together.
Put in large baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: creamy turkey and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing as directed.
Stir in 1/2 can onion bits.
Spread over bottom of greased 9-inch baking dish.
Put broccoli spear flowerets around the edge of dish.
In a saucepan, combine soup and milk until hot.
Remove from heat and add sour cream and turkey.
Pour over broccoli and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle the rest of onion bits over turkey. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, beat other ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and carrots.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kriss kringle cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, sifted with salt and soda. Add oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, marshmallow and peanut butter.
Beat until well blended and quickly pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: golfer's beef stew
directions: Stir the meat, soups and wine together in crock-pot. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. During last hour, add Kitchen Bouquet and flour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: buffet surprise
directions: Place meat in 4-quart pot.
Dump drained kraut on top of meat. Next, put sugar in pot.
On top, pour tomatoes.
Put onion and apple slices in the pot.
Grind pepper over everything.
Cover pot and simmer until meat falls apart, usually about 4 hours.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Make into patties. Fry slowly in 4 tablespoons fat until brown.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini in mucco.
Cool and put into pie crust. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Combine oil, eggs and strawberries.
Stir into flour mixture until well moistened.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with buttercream frosting (optional).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, leaving out salt. Drain and put in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Mix the remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour the mixture over broccoli. Sprinkle buttered dry bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: viola repp's chocolate covered cherryettes
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter, gradually adding powdered sugar, vanilla and almond flavorings.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.

title: river wildlife pilaf
directions: Combine beef broth and wild rice in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Saute long grain rice and barley in 1/2 cup butter in a larger skillet, over medium-high heat, for 5 to 6 minutes or until rice and barley are lightly browned.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine sour cream, Miracle Whip and salt.
Serve as a dip for vegetables.

title: e-z broccoli and mushroom bake
directions: Boil
broccoli	until
slightly
crisp; drain broccoli. Combine
soup
and	cheese	in
saucepan and cook until cheese melts.
Add
broccoli to mixture and pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and beat well, then add eggs, one at a time.
Gently stir in 7-Up.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine in given order.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with white sauce.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and cottage cheese together.
Add cornbread mix, salt, onion, butter and broccoli. Beat until blended.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in 8 or 9-inch round pan.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and water or milk.
Add the dry ingredients, then fold in the oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: suzie bodenhamer's chocolate pie
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken escort casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and chicken broth. Water chestnuts and pimento may be added.
Put 3/4 of the cracker crumbs into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place the chicken mixture on top of the crumbs.
Add remainder of the crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Very good luncheon dish served with fresh fruit.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: In a large skillet, add oil to 1/4-inch deep.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, until lightly browned and blistered, about 10 seconds per side.
Drain on paper towels. Prepare ground beef and taco seasoning according to package directions.
Spread 2 tablespoons refried beans on each tortilla shell.
Top with 2 tablespoons each of beef and salsa.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and garnish with olives and green onions. Broil pizzas 8-inches from heat, about 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: my pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles corn meal.
Stir in water and mix well.
Mixture will be thick.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Then make pie crust as needed.
Roll out pie crust on floured surface.
Bake at 400°.
This can also be rolled into pie crust and frozen whole until ready to use.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Parboil cut potatoes and drain off water.
Saute onion in butter until lightly golden, then add ground meat and seasonings. Cook for about 5 minutes.
Butter casserole.
Alternate a layer of potatoes with a layer of meat, ending with potatoes.
Mix eggs, dry mint, salt and pepper together.
Beat lightly and pour over potato casserole.
Bake in 425° oven for about 45 minutes, until done.

title: honey wheat casserole bread
directions: Using butter, grease a 1/2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix 1/2 cup bread flour, whole wheat flour, nonfat dry milk, yeast, salt, honey and vegetable oil, with mixer on low speed; mix until blended.
While mixing, add hot water.
Continue mixing until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining cup of bread flour, gradually mixing at high speed until smooth.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine rice, beans and onion. In a separate bowl, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, relish and chili powder. Toss with rice mixture. Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Just before serving, stir in green pepper.

title: fruit slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
If desired, garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Combine all other ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (consider oven temperature).

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stir until mixed well. Chill until served.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Melt butter; drizzle over top.
Bake for about 40 minutes.
(It may take longer.
Test with knife to see if it is set as you would a pumpkin pie.)
Serve with whipped topping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt and mustard.
Grease 13 x 9 pan or Pyrex dish.
Put bread on bottom and add sausage and cheese on top.
Pour sauce over all.	Refrigerate overnight.	Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour on cream cheese layer.
Allow to thicken.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with pecans.
Chill a few hours.
Serve!

title: 10 minute lemon raspberry pie
directions: Spoon 1/2
cup of whipped topping into a decorating bag with medium star tip.

title: pasty casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Remove fat.
Combine all ingredients and place in a greased, floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add additional 1/2 cup crumbs to top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Measure into sifter flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Measure into a cup the milk and vanilla.
Measure into large bowl the
Crisco.
Have ready 5 egg whites, beaten to a meringue with 1/2 cup sugar.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Dice onions.
In casserole dish in layers, start with potatoes.
Sprinkle onions; crush approximately 6 or 8 crackers and sprinkle.
Dot with slices of margarine and sliced cheese.
Cover evenly.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, then pour in milk until casserole dish is half full.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In a bowl mix
Ricotta,
cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.	In
a
greased	13
x
9 x 2-inch pan layer 1/2 cup
spaghetti
sauce,
4 noodles and 1/2 cheese
mixture.
Repeat.
Top
with noodles, remaining sauce, then remaining
Mozzarella cheese.	Pour 1 cup of water around edges.
Bake
covered
at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before cutting.
Freezes well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs, shortening and salt.
Add the sour milk. Sift flour and soda.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven. Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and chopped onion.
Mix mustard, molasses and catsup. Add beans to mixture and stir well.
Place in covered bean pot and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Sift and add the flour and soda.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil hen; take off bone and cut into small pieces.
Cook onion, celery and bell pepper on low heat in margarine.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add chicken, onion, celery, pimento and soups.
Pour in baking dish; sprinkle cheese over same.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
This freezes well.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef with seasonings. Boil noodles in salted water. Drain.

Place 1/4 of the noodles in 1-quart casserole. Top with 1/2 of the beef mixture, 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/4 cup of the cheese. Repeat the layers, ending with the cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir
in
salt,
pork
and beans, barbecue sauce, brown
sugar
and
onion and heat until bubbly. Pour into 2 quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half.
Place cut side down
around
edge of casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for
to 30 minutes until brown.
This is suitable for freezing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except the last two.
Toss lightly and spread in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat fat in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion, pepper and meat. Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Add next 6 ingredients. Cover.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally, to avoid sticking.
Add more water if mixture gets too thick.
Combine garlic and salt; add with beans to meat mixture.
Heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix curry powder, garlic salt, sugar, horseradish, onion and vinegar.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with cherry tomatoes and bite-size pieces of other raw vegetables.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and paprika chicken.
Roll the chicken in flour.
Place the chicken in baking pan or skillet (that has been sprayed with Pam).
Drizzle Crisco oil over the chicken.
Bake in a 400° oven until the chicken is done and golden brown.
Be sure to turn the chicken over during baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Heat jello and crushed pineapple until jello melts.
Cool. Mix buttermilk and whipped topping together until well blended. Add to jello and congeal.

title: spinach delight
directions: Place cooked spinach and mushrooms in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and water chestnuts.
Spread Welsh Rarebit evenly over top.
Garnish with French fried onions.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can make ahead and freeze 2 to 3 weeks.

title: potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges, about 6 wedges from each potato. In large plastic bag or bowl with lid, combine flour, cheese, salt, pepper and chicken seasoning.
Add potatoes and shake.
Put 2 tablespoons margarine in a large flat baking pan and melt. Empty entire bag onto baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Add sausage, potatoes, sauerkraut, apple, and apple juice. In a small bowl, mix brown sugar, caraway seed and flour. Stir into saucepan with above ingredients. Simmer from 30 to 40 minutes. Stir occasionally. Just before serving, put on crumbled bacon.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In blender, combine the first banana, oil, vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and dash of salt.
Cover and blend until smooth. Transfer mixture to a screw-top jar; cover and chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let come to a rolling boil (3 minutes).
Add nuts and peanut butter.
Pour in buttered pan and cool; cut.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400 degrees.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shell on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350 degrees.
In Skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned; drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat according to pkg directions.
In a small mixing bowl, combine refried beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce; mix well.
Layer half of refried bean mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Top with half of seasoned meat, 1 cup cheddar cheese and chips.
Repeat layers, excluding chips.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with lettuce and tomato; add additional taco sauce to taste.

title: kid's fun dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 (7-inch) glazed flower pot or 10 small.

title: cheese sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage links in heavy skillet, remove from skillet and drain on paper towel, cut crust from bread slices, roll bread with rolling pin until very thin.
Combine cheese and butter and spread on both sides of bread slices.
Roll up each sausage link in a slice of bread.
Place seam down on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut each into 4 pieces and serve hot.
Yields 64 canapes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute beef until pink disappears and add onion.
Pour off excess fat.
Add remainder of ingredients (not cheese) and simmer for 1 hour.
Place a few cubes of cheese in serving bowl before pouring in soup.

title: everyday thanksgiving(slow cooker)
directions: Place turkey in slow cooker. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over turkey. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and let set for 1 hour.
Squeeze out cabbage with hands.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage.
Let cool and put in freezer boxes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Cool partially. Add egg, bread crumbs and parsley.
Stir in cheese.
Cook shells in boiling water until firm (almost done).
Cook more than 18 shells to allow for cracking.
Cool on a paper towel.
Stuff shells with beef mixture.
Pour 1/4 of the sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange shells in pan and pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut both ends off squash.
Clean out all inside.
Work in crackers, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Stuff meat inside squash.
Mix tomato paste and Italian seasoning, garlic powder. Pour all over squash and cover and bake for 45 minutes in 300° heated oven until squash is done.

title: easy supper rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased muffin tin. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6.

title: harvest soup(cheap, healthy and delicious)
directions: Spray wide 4 to 5-quart pan with cooking spray.
Crumble turkey into pan; add onion, oregano and herb seasoning.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until turkey is no longer pink and onion is soft, but not brown (5 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, carrots, potato, broth, tomato juice, wine and Worcestershire.
Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and boil gently for 20 minutes.
Add pasta.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Add zucchini and boil gently, uncovered, until pasta is tender. Add pepper seasoning.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt. In another bowl combine eggs, bananas, oil, milk and vanilla.
Add to the flour mixture until combines.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: special cheese ring
directions: Mix cheese, pecans, mayonnaise, black pepper, cayenne pepper and onion.
Mold into desired shape.
Place in the refrigerator until chilled.
When ready to serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Using 1 tablespoon batter, roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; press down with sugar coated fork.
Use fork again to make a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet with metal pancake turner.
Cool on rack.
Keep in cookie tin.
Enjoy!
Makes 27 cookies.

title: country sausage and potatoes au gratin
directions: Saute onion and kielbasa in oil until onion is tender.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook until broccoli is heated through and cheese is melted.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain, stir in tomato sauce, beans and cumin seed.
Add garlic salt; simmer.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Line pie plate.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a heavy skillet and cook slowly to the thread stage at 230°.
Add peanuts.
Stir and cook these ingredients just beyond the hard crack stage, 301° to 302°. Remove from heat.
Stir in the butter, soda and vanilla until blended.
Pour the brittle onto a greased surface.
Turn it at once and stretch until thin.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: crescent lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meats and then drain.
Add garlic, onion, parsley, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer five minutes (add a little water if necessary).

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; dredge in flour.
(Cut chicken crosswise into 1-inch strips.)
Reserve remaining flour.
In large skillet, heat butter; add chicken and brown.
Transfer to heated platter.
Add shallots; saute briefly.
Add wine.
Cook liquid over high heat until nearly evaporated while scraping loose brown particles.
Add reserved flour; stir to thick paste.
Sprinkle with tarragon.
Stir in stock.
Return chicken to skillet and cook until tender, about 25 minutes, adding broth as needed.
Transfer chicken to heated plate; keep hot.
Add cream to skillet; heat, stirring and pour sauce over chicken.

title: summertime salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serve on a bed of lettuce and garnish with crushed walnuts or pecans.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Cream sugar, egg, and shortening in mixing bowl.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into creamed mixture.
Add mashed banana. Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 min.
Check with toothpick.
Cool on rack. Makes 16 slices.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in boiling water.
Add gelatin.
Put in refrigerator to cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: baked omelet
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir until frothy.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add salt.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Place egg yolks in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and beat. Slowly add cream sauce which has been cooled slightly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: two thumbs up salsa
directions: Mix everything, then place in food processor and pulse quickly 5 or 6 times.
Makes enough for a party!

title: rye bread
directions: Place yeast and pinch of sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put everything except the yeast and the flour into the bowl and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add yeast, rye flour and 3 cups of white flour.
Mix well.
Gradually add the last cup of flour until the mass cleans off the sides of the bowl.
This may take slightly more or slightly less than the 4 cups of flour.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Put thawed rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle sugar and Jell-O over the rhubarb.
Melt oleo and pour into cake mix; blend and crumble over the rhubarb mixture. Cover all with water.
Cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: southern peas and rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain on absorbent paper.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender-crisp.
Stir in rice and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Add tomato and bacon; toss lightly.
Spoon rice into serving dishes and top with peas.
Serves 6.

title: lucille's dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in cooled milk.
Add salt, shortening, sugar and water.
Add flour, a little at a time, mix well after each addition.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth.
Cover with warm damp towel.
Let rise until double.
Roll 1/3-inch thick. Cut into 2-inch circles.
Crease middle with dull knife.
Brush with butter; fold along crease.
Place close together in well-greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise to treble size. Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.
You may use bread machine's dough cycle.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Add rice, cheese, soup, milk and mix together.
Pour into a 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: mince pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and dot butter over the top.
Put mixture in pie pastry and cover with pastry top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Crumble bacon; drain again on paper.
Combine bacon drippings, olive oil, vinegar and sugar in jar.
Cover, shake well and set aside.

title: char-grilled chicken
directions: Place liquid ingredients in large bowl and stir.
Add garlic and chicken and let marinate for several hours.
Turn bowl and shake several times during marinating time.
Prepare outside grill and cook.
Really good.

title: green stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate to set.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Beat softened butter or margarine 2 minutes, until creamy. Gradually add sugar; beat at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes, until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Gradually add 1/4 of the flour at a time alternately with the sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavoring. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl several times with spatula to mix batter.
Spoon batter into a tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, in center of oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar together. Add egg, water and oil. Grease muffin pans and fill 2/3 full. Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: christmas pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
