Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: green tomato chow-chow
directions: Cover tomatoes with salt and let stand for 2 to 3 hours.
Cut onions, hot peppers, bell peppers, sugar and apple vinegar. Drain tomatoes and mix with mixture.
Simmer until onions and tomatoes are tender.
Makes 14 pints.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain and dry cherries.
Combine margarine and corn syrup. Stir in confectioners sugar.
Knead mixture until smooth.
Chill if too soft.
Mold mixture around cherries, then cool.
Dip in melted chocolate to coat cherries.
Put on waxed paper.
Keep in refrigerator in covered container 1 to 2 weeks to ripen.

title: peanut butter sauce for chicken or pork
directions: Cook onion, garlic and cumin over low heat until cooked and soft.
Add chicken broth and 1/2 cup milk.
Moisten bread crumbs in remaining milk; let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add peanut butter, turmeric, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until sauce is smooth and thick.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together.
Slice meat to desired thickness.
Soak meat in sauce for 12 hours in a cool place (refrigerator).
Place tinfoil lining on the bottom of the oven to catch excess sauce.
Poke toothpicks through meat slices and hang meat on oven racks.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
(The less time baked, the more moist.)

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt over double boiler or microwave.
Add cornflakes.
Shape into wreath.
Garnish with red M&M's.

title: quick fix taco casserole
directions: In saucepan prepare
cheddar broccoli rice according to directions (I add 1/2 box chopped broccoli and 1/2 cup chopped green onions).
In skillet	brown
ground meat in Crisco until tender.
Dissolve taco mix in
water
and
pour
over meat and stir well.	Combine together with rice and broccoli, then pour into baking dish.
Cover
with
grated
cheese
and bake until cheese is melted.

title: kiwi dessert
directions: Layer cake in bottom of trifle bowl.
Add pudding, Cool Whip, kiwi, bananas, then strawberries.
Repeat.
Put Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large deep-dish bowl, mix egg whites, sugar, crumbs, pecans and coconut and stir by hand. Pour into pie shell and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until glossy and set. Do not overbake. (It is firm near the edges but moist and chewy in the center.) Serve warm with sliced bananas and whipped cream.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Beat the cooked squash and carrots together.
Then beat in all other ingredients.
Turn into greased shallow casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This can be prepared in the morning and refrigerated until time to bake.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: pecan date cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix nuts and fruit.
Beat eggs, vanilla and salt; add flour mixture.
Pour over fruit and nut mixture; work with hands until thoroughly blended.
Bake in loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours. Remove wax paper immediately after baking.

title: strawberry pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water and cornstarch until transparent. Remove from fire; stir in 1/2 package of strawberry jello. Cool and pour over berries in pie shell and chill.

title: brownie fudge pie
directions: Bake pie shell in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
In saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate chips.
In a bowl, mix Bisquick, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture. Stir well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the beef in a Teflon skillet.
Add celery and onions; cook until tender.
Stir in soup and thyme.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon potatoes around the edge.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until piping hot.
Serves 4, 299 calories per serving.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine, then sprinkle over it in order: graham cracker crumbs, flaked coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips, then drizzle milk over it and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Very rich.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion over medium heat.
Drain off fat, then spoon into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce, mushrooms and cheese. Combine Bisquick mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before serving.
To serve, cut in squares and turn pieces upside-down on plate.

title: b l t dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread sticks, together. Makes a wonderful dip for your bread sticks.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and make little balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 8 layer dip or mexican dip
directions: Chop your tomato first, so it can be draining while you are fixing the first three layers.

title: chris' cajun gumbo
directions: Gumbo is best made by combining game and tame meats, if you like game.
If not, make it tame.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix. Roll out about 3/4 inch thick. Cut and bake in hot oven 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make sure shrimp are well chilled before mixing.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In a
large
skillet,
melt butter; add meat, onion and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown.	Drain excess fat.
Stir in flour, then
add
soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes on	low
heat.
Stir
in
sour
cream; heat to serving temperature.
Serve over buttered noodles.	Serves 6.

title: griddle french fries
directions: Heat griddle using a little oil to start.
Add potatoes and sprinkle
with
seasonings of your choice.
As the griddle gets dry, add some butter.
Cook until crispy outside.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter. Stir in potatoes until all are coated lightly. Dip with spoon and drop on wax paper. Let cool.

title: broccoli cauliflower bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a covered casserole dish.
(Can substitute cream of celery soup and add croutons or bread crumbs).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a hard boil. Cook one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook hen or fryer until it comes off bone.
Put chicken (boned) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon cream of chicken soup over chicken, undiluted.
Moisten Pepperidge Farm dressing with some of the broth and put on top of chicken.
Melt margarine and spoon over dressing.
Put in 400° oven for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well together.
Make a loaf and place it in a 7 x 9-inch pan.
Pour tomato juice over meat loaf with one inch of juice all around loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Cream
margarine
well.
Add sugar slowly and mix well. Drop in
egg
yolks
and beat 1/2 hour.
Add vanilla, nuts and pineapple.
Arrange
layer
of
crumbs in buttered pan, then a layer
of
fruit mixture and then crumbs, continuing until pan is filled.
Top
with crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: mama's good cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in a greased round Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 375°.

title: easy pour pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In frypan, brown hamburger and onion. Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch pan.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt, oregano, pepper, milk and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into pan so covers the bottom of pan.
Arrange meat, mushrooms or anything else you want on pizza. Pour pizza sauce over this and top with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes. Careful not to overbake.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
In a 9 x 11-inch baking dish, layer hamburger mixture in bottom.
Slice and layer cheese on top.
In small bowl, mix soup and milk; pour on top of cheese.
Layer Tater Tots evenly over top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Mix graham crackers, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and soak overnight covered in water.
Drain lentils, reserving liquid to make 10 cups.
Add lentils.
Cook, covered, 2 hours with a ham bone.
Add onion, celery, carrots, garlic and sugar.
Remove meat from bone and add to syrup.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and mix in 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir into syrup until blended.
Simmer another 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: In a large soup pot, heat the olive oil over medium high heat.
Add the sausage, onion and garlic and cook for 5 to 6 minutes or until no pink remains in the sausage, stirring frequently to break up the meat.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil; simmer for twenty minutes.
Add the ditalini and simmer an additional ten minutes, stirring frequently to keep the pasta from sticking to the bottom of the pot.
Best if made a day ahead so the flavors meld.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°. Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk. Sift flour and cinnamon together and add to above mixture.
Spread thinly on a large cookie sheet.
Press chopped pecans into dough. Spread beaten egg white over the top. Bake for 1 hour.
Do not cook until brown or they will taste scorched. Cut into squares or strips while hot.

title: pollo papale
directions: Francaise the chicken and eggplant.
Cut up chicken, leaving the lower part of the wing bone attached to the breast.
Tenderize the chicken breast until it's flat and thin, i.e., pound with hammer.
Can also francaise the dark meat and place under the breast.
In bowl, mix eggs, parsley, white pepper and salt.
In second bowl, put flour.
Dip chicken in flour.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Fry chicken until golden brown in vegetable oil.
Set chicken aside.
Cut eggplant into 1/8-inch thin slices.
Dip eggplant in flour, then in egg mixture.
Fry until golden brown in vegetable oil; set eggplant aside.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients. Mix and add soups and water; season to taste. Add rice. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 2 hours. During last 1/2 hour, sprinkle 1 cup chow mein noodles on top.

title: warm apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 2 qt. casserole.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugars and cinnamon.
Cut in butter to make crumbs.
Cover apples with crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: "good" cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Reserve 1/4 cup.
Pat remainder in bottom of pan.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Stir in cooled gelatin.
Whip the cream to soft peaks.
Fold into cheese-gelatin mixture. Spoon over crust; sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in greased casserole dish. Brown pork chops on each side, not completely done, but brown. Place chops on rice. Cover rice and chops with soups. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Use a 9x13 in. square buttered dish.
Place pineapple on bottom of dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour cake mix over pineapple and brown sugar.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: appetizer chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints; remove wing tip.
Wash and pat dry. Combine remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange wings, single layer, in marinade.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 370°
for about 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: jewels
directions: Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cut 4 down and 8 across.
Delicious and very rich!

title: helen's refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour warm milk and water in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle yeast and stir well.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Stir well.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Add 3 cups flour to mixture and beat well by hand.
Add melted shortening and stir well.
Mix other 3 cups of flour and knead enough by hand in bowl until smooth.
Allow to rise in well-greased bowl until about double.
This should rise in warm place about 2 hours.
Work down and place in well-greased bowl, well covered in refrigerator until ready to use.
Then drop into well-greased muffin tins, cover and let rise again until doubled before baking.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Makes about 30 rolls.
The dough can be refrigerated approximately 1 week and cook rolls as needed.

title: lemon chess pie(good!)
directions: Combine sugar, cornmeal, flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat eggs well. Add sugar mixture and mix well. Add buttermilk, butter, lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until top is golden brown and custard is set.
(There will be some free butter at
this point but it will be absorbed as the pie cools.)
Remove to rack and
cool completely. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, sifted with soda.
Add oatmeal and chopped nuts (mixed with a spoon). Bake at 400° for about 9 minutes.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Work butter, flour, sugar and nuts until crumbly. Work into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cashew nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 2 cookie sheets. Beat butter and brown sugar in mixing bowl at medium speed. Beat sour cream, egg, and vanilla into butter and brown sugar mixture. Stir flour, baking soda, and salt together and add to egg mixture and beat. Fold in cashews. Drop by tsp. Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In a greased 13x9 pan, spread the rice; place chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with soup mix. Combine the soup, salt, pepper and milk and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300 degrees for 2 1/4 hours. Cover with foil for the first 1 1/4 hours.

title: maple walnut cream pie
directions: Fold everything together.
Place in a baked pie crust and freeze until ready to serve.

title: scripture cake
directions: Make as any other cake and follow Solomon's recipe for bringing up a good boy - Proverbs 23:14.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower and mayo.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: glorified rice
directions: In a large bowl, mix jello with sugar and 1 cup boiling water. Add cooked rice to the jello mixture.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
If too thick, add a little cold water.
Let set in refrigerator, stirring occasionally until set.

title: double brownies
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake on greased sheet cake pan.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: microwave chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 12 x 7-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine butter or margarine, onion, garlic and oregano.
Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave at full power (High) for 5 minutes, or until onion is tender.
Turn chicken pieces over in the butter mixture to coat.
Arrange chicken with thicker side towards outside of dish. Spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken, coating completely.
Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave at High for 12 minutes.
Turn chicken up.
Spoon sauce over; re-cover with wrap and microwave at High 12 to 14 additional minutes, or until tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano grated cheese.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Add peanut butter, soda and oatmeal.
Stir in nuts, M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not brown; leave on sheet for 1 minute before removing.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: flounder with crab stuffing
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, crab, bread crumbs and flounder; salt and pepper to taste, mixing well.
Cut fillets into 8 pieces and spread each piece with crab meat mixture.
Roll to enclose filling and place seam side down in a shallow baking pan.

title: norma jean's skillet candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a heavy skillet.
Cook on medium heat until it boils.
Add sweet potatoes.
Cook at low heat for about 20 minutes, turning several times.
In about five minutes, you may add drained pineapple chunks and a few raisins and nuts if you like.
If using pineapple, use the juice to replace water.
If not using the pineapple, you may add thin slices of orange.

title: spicy cajun chicken and sausage pasta
directions: Put butter in a large pot.
Saute red pepper, green pepper and onions.
Then add chopped tomatoes, chicken, sausage and mushrooms. Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, Tabasco sauce, black pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Cook another 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Boil linguini as per directions on package; drain.
Pour 1/4 cup oil over linguini.
Pour chicken and sausage mixture over linguini; toss lightly.
Serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables together in a large bowl.

title: mom's chili
directions: Saute butter, celery and ground chuck.
Drain grease; add tomatoes, sauce, salt, sugar and chili powder.
Simmer 1 hour. Add beans.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Heat to boiling the crushed pineapple and juice.
Then dissolve Jell-O in pineapple and cool.
Cream the cream cheese gradually with the milk.
Mix with pineapple mixture.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with syrup, blending well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Put in tube pan, lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn on rack; peel off paper. Cool and serve with cream.

title: ice cream
directions: Get a bowl and spoon and start eating.
Don't forget the ice cream in the bowl.

title: peanut butter crumble bars
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening, peanut butter and egg until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Reserve 1 cup dough.
Press remaining dough into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add water and seasonings.
Then pour honey over chicken.
Bake in 375° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Chicken will be a golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix like pie crust and add 1 beaten egg.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Flatten into 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: fruit fluff easy
directions: In a large bowl, fold together all ingredients.
Pile into pretty bowl and garnish with whole pecans.
Chill.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Stir chicken, chicken soup, celery soup and bread into baking dish or pan.
Roll crackers until fine. Melt butter; stir in crackers and crumble over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Will serve 4 or 5 people.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine peanut butter, sugar and egg (batter will be stiff).
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Scoop level tablespoon of batter and roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until browned.
(This recipe does not use any flour.) Makes 2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in water with salt.
Cook on low heat until all water is gone.
Combine onion and broccoli.
Place in casserole dish and thaw in microwave for approximately 5 minutes.
Add cheese to cooked rice.
Combine milk and soup with rest of ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Add Durkee onions and shredded Cheddar cheese toward end of baking.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Drop in 24 Ritz crackers, one at a time.
Do not stir.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle good with cinnamon and cut up 1/2 stick oleo on top.
Put on top crust.
(Top crust is optional.)
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with scoop of vanilla ice cream (optional).

title: artichoke spaghetti sauce
directions: Serves 6.
Saute artichokes, butter, olives and mushrooms in pan for 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: fideo
directions: Brown hamburger in separate pan; set aside.
Fry crushed capellini, onion and bell pepper in hot oil; add beef broth, tomatoes, parsley and hamburger.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 4 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Sift the first four ingredients.
Add the nuts.
Melt margarine, remove from heat and mix with brown sugar.
Add 1 tablespoon hot water.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, a small amount at a time.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle the chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or 30 to 35 minutes for doubled recipe (use 13 x 9-inch pan).

title: peanut bars
directions: Mix ingredients and pat into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.

title: cavatina
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; add tomato sauce, mushrooms and spices.
Cook egg noodles (not done).
Grease dish; layer meat, noodles, cheese, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in pan; bring to a boil. Stir constantly; boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove; stir in marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until all melted. Pour into foil-lined or glass 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, then cut.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Shape into loaf and place in loaf pan.
Cover with 1 can undiluted mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. (Soup makes excellent gravy.)
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Alternate 1/2 cup milk with rest of dry ingredients as you mix it all together.
Add zucchini last.
Mix in.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and flavoring, then alternately the flour.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf or tube pan one hour at 325°.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Mix lightly but thoroughly. Shape into 4 dozen small balls about 1-inch in diameter. Place on a cookie sheet and brown in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, turning once.

title: frosting
directions: Combine the 1/2 cup powdered sugar, shortening, vanilla.
Add the remainder of the powdered sugar.
Add egg whites.

title: kathy's dressing
directions: Blend very well.
Store in airtight container in fridge.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and top with bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in small amount of butter.
Cook broccoli until almost tender and drain.
Add onions, soup, cheese and butter.
Cover and simmer until onions are tender.
Add mushrooms and almonds.
Serve hot with Melba toast or corn chips.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Grease 15 medium muffin cups.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Immediately after baking, roll puffs in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: plain ole goulash
directions: Boil macaroni shells 8 to 10 minutes, then drain.
Saute onion until tender.
Cook ground beef until browned and drain. Mix tomato soup, tomatoes and onions with the ground beef and macaroni.
Simmer on low about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Sift together sifted flour and baking soda.
Add alternately with 1 cup of buttermilk.
Fold in 3 egg whites (stiffly beaten).
Stir in coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour into 3 well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until well done and brown. Cool before frosting.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in olive oil.
Add onion, green pepper, carrot and salt.
Mix in cup and pour over chops:
water, vinegar, brown sugar, apple, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours (or until completely cooked).
Serve over rice.

title: squash spaghetti(microwave)
directions: Look for good yellow/orange color; hard squash that is heavy. Wash squash.
Pierce with tip of sharp knife in several places. Allows steam to escape.
Place squash on paper towel in microwave. Microwave uncovered on High 18 to 23 minutes, turning over after 8 minutes, until tender when pierced with tip of sharp knife.
Let stand uncovered 10 minutes.
Cut crosswise in half; remove seeds and fibers.
Scrape fork across squash to pull flesh into strands. Serve with spaghetti or clam cause or serve with sprinkled grated cheese.
Yields 4 servings, 60 calories per serving.

title: string beans with shrimp
directions: Combine string beans, garlic, onion and shrimp in large bowl. Toss.
Whisk together vinegar, lemon juice, anchovy paste, basil, salt and oil.
Pour dressing over beans and shrimp.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature for an hour or cover and refrigerate for up to 8 hours before serving.
Serve at room temperature.
Enjoy!!

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: Pour syrup over vegetables and refrigerate for 3 days.
Will keep for months and will freeze.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream lard (Crisco), sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° until cookie starts to turn light brown around edges (about 5 to 8 minutes).

title: shrimp and scallops norfolk(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until frothy.
Pour into large saute pan.
Heat over medium heat.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: beaufort stew
directions: Fill a large pot with water and bring to a boil.
Add seasoning bag, potatoes and onions.
Add sausage (allow 10 to 15 minutes cooking time) and then corn (allow 7 to 10 minutes cooking time).
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink (5 to 7 minutes).
Total time is 25 to 35 minutes.

title: corn matzatlan
directions: Drain corn saving 3 teaspoons of liquid.
Melt cream cheese in the saved liquid; add bell peppers, onions and green chilies.
Add corn; mix together and heat.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add onions and then all the other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sugarless pineapple shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend for 60 seconds at low speed.
Serves one.

title: shrimp with artichokes
directions: Butter a 2-quart baking dish and arrange artichoke hearts in a single layer.
Cover them with cooked shrimp.
In a small saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons of butter and saute mushrooms for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Spread mushrooms over shrimp.
Melt the remaining 3 tablespoons of butter, add the flour and mix well. Whisk in the milk, sherry and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour this sauce evenly over the top of the mushrooms and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes, then lower to 350°.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: lemon blue cheese chicken
directions: In bowl mix together corn oil, lemon juice, cheese, flavor enhancer, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Place on broiler pan, skin side down.
Cook, turning chicken frequently, basting with additional sauce about 45 minutes or until browned.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: freezer peach jam
directions: Measure peaches into a large bowl.
Stir in sugar and citric acid.
Mix well and let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Mix water and pectin in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir into peach mixture.
Continue stirring for 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into 5 one-cup (1/2 pint) containers. Cover tightly.
Let stand until set, then store in freezer.
(If jam is to be used in 2 or 3 weeks, it may be stored in refrigerator.)
For softer spread, use 3 cups of prepared fruit and 5 cups of sugar.
Proceed as directed.
Apricots may be used in place of peaches.

title: stuffed mushrooms(smoked cheese and salami)
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove and chop stems.
Place stems in small bowl with onion or butter, if included in recipe.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Arrange caps on paper towel lined plate with larger caps to outside.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, until heated, rotating plate once or twice.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mound in mushroom caps.

title: cheese eyeballs
directions: Combine cheese and butter. Add salt, paprika and flour, mix well. Measure approx. one tsp. of mix and form cheese mixture around olive with pimentos showing. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut and cube cheese into small cubes and add chili to a crock-pot.
To make it easier melt cheese in microwave and then transfer to crock-pot to keep warm and serve with tortilla chips. This is an awesome party dip.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Combine 2 Tbsp. cheese and bacon; mix well.
In 2 1/2 quart bowl layer spinach, cheese mixture, mushrooms, onion, and peas.

title: strawberry charlotte russe
directions: Put jello in a large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Combine strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Combine with gelatin mixture. Chill to consistency of beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: baked liver
directions: For beef or pork liver, cut in serving size pieces.
Dip 3 or 4 times in very hot water.
Salt to taste and roll in flour.
Melt shortening in a heavy skillet.
Place liver in skillet. Put an onion slice on each piece. Bake at 375° until tender and brown. Turn over.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers, pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together; boil until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dry jello.
Let cool.
Fill pie shell with strawberries (leave whole or slice).
Pour jello filling over berries and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: baked chicken with wine
directions: Bread chicken with flour.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken pieces in a baking pan; season with pepper.
Cover chicken with onion soup mix and pour wine over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Very easy.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Grate or cut chocolate.
Mix all together and cook, stirring constantly (takes about 10 minutes or 238° on candy thermometer) to a soft ball stage.
Put in cold water and beat until creamy.
If it becomes too hard, add a little milk and beat.

title: little cheesecake puffs
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Line little cupcake tinfoil papers with a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each.
No muffin pan is needed.
Fill liners 3/4 full of cheese mixture. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool and cover with pie filling. Chill.
Makes 2 dozen, depending on foil tins.

title: apricot bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread crumbs and apricots in dish.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Top with coconut and nuts, pressing gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: miss susie young's christmas fruitcake
directions: Step One:
Combine the following as you would any cake mix. First, beat eggs and butter.
Add sugar.
Sift 4 cups flour with soda and spices.
Add to eggs mixture alternately with buttermilk, blackberry jam and grape juice.
Set aside.

title: play dough(do not eat)
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture forms a large ball.
Remove and knead until lumps are removed.
Food coloring and/or flavoring may be added.
Store in airtight bag or container.

title: savannah red rice
directions: In a large frying pan, fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan. Crumble and reserve.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in bacon grease until tender.
Add rice, tomatoes, crumbled bacon and seasoning.
Cook on top of the stove for 10 minutes.
Pour into large greased casserole dish, cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in casserole dish.
Mix potato soup and water; pour over cabbage.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with croutons and extra cheese if desired.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: savory spread for tiny sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending until smooth.
Spread on slices of cocktail bread.
Put a thin slice of cucumber on top of spread.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Can be used with thinly sliced boiled eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: crisp toffee bars
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour, nuts and chocolate chips by hand.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: traveling taco
directions: Layer on pizza pan in order.
Serve with nacho chips to scoop. Better if made ahead by at least an hour to chill.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs, top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Country Potatoes:
Peel and quarter 6 to 8 potatoes.
Boil and drain.
Add 3 cups milk, 1/4 cup butter and a handful of chopped parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When butter is melted and milk is hot, add 2 tablespoons flour, dissolved in water, to the mixture.
Fold lightly.
Cook until thickened.

title: pot roast
directions: In a large, heavy pan, brown meat in shortening; pour off fat. Add soup and water; cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Remove meat from pan.
Gradually blend 1/4 cup water into flour.
Slowly stir into gravy.
Cook; stir until thickened.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large pot, cover chicken with water.
Cook uncovered until done.
Debone and defat chicken, saving stock.
Bring the stock to a boil and cook spaghetti (most of the water should be absorbed).
Add cheese and chicken.
Stir until cheese is melted. Add 1 or 2 cans soup.
Can be served immediately or put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise and put in jars.
Add 1 onion sliced 2 inches thick for each quart of cucumbers and add 1 head of dill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Add egg, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Put stuffing mix on top of mixture and drizzle over with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus, petits pois and mushroom casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and arrange half of it in a buttered 6-cup casserole.
In a bowl, mix gently the peas, soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Spoon 1/2 the mixture into casserole.
Add remainder of asparagus; top with remaining mixture.
Toss crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crisscross potatoes
directions: Rub butter over washed potatoes.
Cut potatoes lengthwise. Make crisscross slashes on cut side of potatoes with sharp knife. Spread cut side with butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Place in baking dish, butter side down.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: children's delight cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water for 5 minutes. Drain well and cool. Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, raisins and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients, add pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1 /2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove baked cookies from pan immediately. Yields 4 dozen.

title: hominy corn casserole
directions: Drain hominy corn and add to cream-style corn.
Put in 1/2 of the margarine and cook in pan for about 15 minutes.
Add pepper and salt.
Melt the other 1/2 of margarine and add crushed crackers.
Layer crackers on top of corn and hominy mixture.
Put in 350° oven and cook until crackers are brown.
(You may add 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese to top of casserole before putting on crushed crackers.)

title: cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Mix in dry cake mix.
Remove 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Pour cherry pie filling on top. Sprinkle the cake/margarine mixture on top.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix milk and beaten egg yolks well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Make a syrup of sugar, cinnamon, water and margarine.
Bring to boil and stir.
Remove from heat and pour over balls in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn upside down on plate or cookie sheet.
Pull apart to serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sherbet to cool.
Then add drained fruit to cool Jell-O mixture.
Add bananas and whipped cream last.
This makes a large salad dish.

title: safari cooler
directions: Put in blender.
Mix.
Pour mixture into a tall glass.
Add 1/4 cup 7-Up.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Dissolve chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream sugar, Crisco, egg yolks and salt.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk alternately with flour.
Dissolve soda in remaining buttermilk.
Add with the chocolate and vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° until cake barely springs back to touch.

title: homemade chocolate frosting
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Heat over low flame but do not boil.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: old fashion banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put in top of double boiler and add milk slowly.
Stir constantly over boiling water until thick.
Occasionally stir while cooking 15 minutes more, uncovered.
Beat egg yolks in a bowl. Stir into custard mixture gradually.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Let cool.
Line bottom of dish with vanilla wafers, bananas and custard.
Repeat layers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
In another bowl, cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat after each.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients and stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage for a king
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook cabbage in small amount of boiling water about 5 minutes.
Lightly brown bread cubes in 1 tablespoon of butter. Arrange in a 2-quart casserole the cabbage, tomato mixture, bread and cheese, ending with bread and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour
in
prepared crust and chill.
Add Cool Whip or whipping cream before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line casserole dish with beef.
Place chicken on top of beef. Pepper chicken only and cover with bacon.
(Wrap bacon like filet mignon.)
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.
Cook 3 hours at 275°, uncovered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: three cheese macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Cook and stir butter, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is slightly tender. Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in cheddar cheese until melted.
Stir in cottage cheese and macaroni.
Place in a casserole dish and top with American cheese slices.
Cook uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 min., or until bubbly and cheese is melted and slightly brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge syrup
directions: Cook all but vanilla until it lightly boils 1 minute, stirring.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn and put in brown bag sprayed with Pam.
Cook sugar, corn syrup and butter on High in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook 1 1/2 more minutes.
Take out and stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Take out and shake.
Repeat 3 to 4 times.
Then pour in bowl and break loose.

title: hot baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, salt, mayonnaise, lemon juice and onions.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix cheese and chips.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Great and easy for luncheons.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the first five ingredients together in a 9 X 13 cake pan.
Cut three holes into the mixture.
In the first hole put the vinegar, in another put the vanilla and in the last put oil.
Pour water over all of them.
Mix with spoon and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: yam and apple bake
directions: Peel yams after cooking.
Steam 1/2-inch yam slices with 1 cup of water.
Do not overcook.
Cut apples in 1/2-inch slices.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, 2 cups of water and margarine in a heavy pan until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and lemon extract. In a 4-quart dish, layer potatoes, sauce, apples and sauce.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients gently and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Do not brown ground beef.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese toast
directions: Put bread in toaster.
Put butter on bread and cheese on top of butter.
Put in microwave for 1 minute.

title: sunday dinner steaks
directions: Dredge steaks in flour and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides in hot oil.
Put steaks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with mushrooms.
Layer onions over top.
Pour gravy which has been mixed with one can water over steaks and onions.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 250° for three to four hours.

title: dot's brownies
directions: Soften butter, cream sugar, break eggs in and mix well.
Add flour and mix all together well, adding vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch greased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, and pepper.
Mix in beans.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Add chips on top and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Use plenty of cheese and taco chips, I also added taco seasoning for more flavor.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased ovenware.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Pour into bowl.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and salt.
Mix and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine margarine and onions; saute in soup pot.
Add water and bring to boil.
Add noodles and salt; boil 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic powder; boil 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese. Do not boil.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms and pepper. Cook slowly for a few minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken-rice-artichoke salad
directions: n and chop artichokes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add mayonnaise at end (I use light).
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.
Great with Ritz crackers!

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan until the Crisco is melted. Pour 3 cups of milk into a large bowl (at least 6-quart). Pour hot mixture into cold milk.	Dissolve yeast as directed and add to liquids or mix in with the dry flour. Stir flour into liquids. Let rise until about doubled and punch down. Can be refrigerated until needed. Pour out dough on floured pastry cloth and knead. Shape rolls into desired shape on a baking sheet or in muffin tin. Let rise in pans until doubled. Bake in a 400° oven for approximately 10 minutes. Can be stored in refrigerator for up to a week.

title: berry yogurt parfait
directions: In dessert or parfait glass, layer yogurt, granola and berries until dish or glass is full, normally 3 layers.
Chill. Serve as dessert, at brunch or for anytime snack.

title: dream salad
directions: Combine juice, gelatin and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil. Turn
off
heat
and
add
marshmallows,
stirring until melted. Cool.
Add
pineapple,
nuts and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 2 balls. Wrap each in clear plastic. These can be frozen and are real good when you have to have a quick snack to carry somewhere.

title: out of this world sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and pour into pie crust.
Top with mixture of marshmallow creme and cool whip.
Garnish with orange slices and serve.

title: apple delight
directions: Preheat oven to
Peel, core and slice apples into bowl. Add 1/2 cup sugar, spices and lemon juice.
Mix lightly and pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend remaining sugar, flour, salt and butter to a crumbly consistency.
Add nuts and sprinkle over the apple mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until the apples are tender and crust nicely browned.
Serve with ice cream.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Cook meat and onion in large skillet until onion is tender. Stir in rice, tomatoes, tomato paste, olives and seasonings.
Turn in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: no guilt granola bars
directions: Blend all the fruits in blender or food processor.
Add fruits to oats.
Let stand for a few minutes for the oats to absorb any liquid from fruits.
Press into a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 4 hours (depending on fruit used).
Cut into bars after 1 hour in oven.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 24 bars.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Beat brown sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Stir in baking mix and walnuts until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: chocolate (beet) cake
directions: Puree the cooked beets; put aside.
Beat together the eggs, brown sugar and oil.
Add beets and the remaining ingredients. Bake in a 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick and easy pork tenderloins
directions: Mix flour and salt and pepper.
Dip meat in milk and then into flour.
Fry meat in medium frying pan in a small amount of olive oil, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions, celery and garlic in same pan until onions are transparent. Return meat to pan.
Cover with peas and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
(This also works great with pork chops.)

title: honey-almond cheesecake
directions: Place a large pan, half-filled with water, on lowest oven rack, with oven at 325°.
Coat 8-inch spring-form pan with nonstick spray.

title: mock wild rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown uncooked rice with the margarine. Heavily butter (or Pam) a standard size casserole dish (1 1/2-quart).
Pour in browned rice, then add consomme and mushrooms with juice, rosemary and salt to taste.
Stir.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until well done at 350° with cover lid. Serves 6.

title: brownies in a jar(holiday gift)
directions: Mix flour and salt together, spoon mixture into a quart jar. Add the following, tapping jar to settle after each addition.

6 tbsp. cocoa, 3/4 cup granulated sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 3/4 cup granulated sugar, 6 tbsp. cocoa, 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1/4 cup white chips, 1/4 cup chocolate chips. Close lid. Tie baking instruction tag to jar.

title: garden club punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ginger ale, until sugar dissolves.
Then add ginger ale.
Serve in punch bowl with ice ring or in pitcher with ice.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients together until the carrots are tender. Serves 4.

title: turkey breast
directions: Saute vegetables in olive oil.
Place turkey in crock-pot. Pour vegetables onto turkey.
Add soup and 1 can water.
Simmer all day.
Enjoy with rice or potatoes.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix baking mix, milk, eggs and onion.
Beat vigorously.
Spread in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon evenly over batter. Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lolly's sour cream date cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and nutmeg, mixing well.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Gently stir in dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 5 minutes on cookie sheet and then remove with spatula.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue biscuits
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and pepper together and cook until done. Drain
excess fat, if necessary.
Add water, catsup and barbecue sauce
and	let
simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Make
homemade biscuits and lay on top and
bake at	350°
until
biscuits are done.
Goes well with salad.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and Doritos.
Spread Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with mashed bananas.
Add chocolate chips, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate avalanche
directions: Use a food processor for easiest preparation.
Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In the top of a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate pieces.
Fit the steel knife blade into the work bowl of a food processor.
Combine melted chocolate, evaporated milk, powdered sugar, walnuts and coconut in the work bowl.
Process until well mixed, 6 to 8 seconds only, stopping to scrape down sides of bowl with a rubber spatula.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand 30 minutes or until set. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 36 balls.

title: korean style burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into four balls and flatten into patties.
You can fry, grill or broil.
You can serve them on a bun like a hamburger or try them with fried rice and stir-fried vegetables.

title: fried pickles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Drain pickles and pat dry with a towel.
Dip pickles in flour mixture, then buttermilk.
Repeat 1 time.
Fry until brown.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: frighteningly good peanut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, heat peanut butter and butter for 5 minutes or until melted.
Remove; stir in seasoned salt.
Gradually add cereals and nuts, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Stir in raisins and peanut butter pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and spread in a 9 X 13 pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and milk until mixture spins a thread.
Pour over corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Pour onto wax paper until cool, then roll into balls.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare pudding.
Melt cream cheese into the pudding.
Cool.
Spread pudding mixture on cooled cake.
Cover pudding with pineapple; layer bananas, side by side.
Cover entire cake.
Cover bananas with Cool Whip.
Put sliced strawberries on top of Cool Whip. Sprinkle chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave brown rice
directions: Brown rice in margarine.
Pour in microwave casserole dish. Pour in soup.
Microwave 23 minutes on 50%, covered.

title: chicken dish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Heat at 375° until warm and bubbly.
May be served with rice or toast points.

title: kari's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add 1 egg at a time and mix well. Add vanilla.
Alternate, adding oatmeal and flour, then add soda. Mix in the grated chocolate bar, then add chocolate chips and Heath Bar Bits.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into cubes.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Saute onion, peppers and celery in bacon drippings until transparent.
Add cooked, drained eggplant slightly mashed.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon crinkle cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
Combine egg whites and water in another small bowl; beat lightly with fork. Set aside.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, chicken broth, butter, sugar, onion and soda; simmer 1 hour.
Heat cream in double boiler.
Add cream to tomato mix.
Ready to serve and enjoy.
It is delicious.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low to medium heat.
Stir occasionally until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Don't boil.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add dry yeast (dissolved in 1 cup warm water).
Mix well.
Add sugar, Crisco and salt.
Mash together well.
Add boiling water; mix this.
Add flour and mix well. Place in pre-oiled large bowl.
Let rise 3 hours.
Knead real stiff on floured board.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Enjoy.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil on low heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients immediately.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch pan, when cool, cut into squares.
Non-fail fudge.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients except soda in a heavy iron skillet.
Cook until peanuts start popping and are well done.
Remove from heat and add soda; mix well.
Pour into well-greased platter.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Mix together onion soup and mushroom soup.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Place in large baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cook the rice in 3 cups water for 5 minutes; drain.
Cook onions in large skillet until clear but not brown.
Mix well all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old world sauerkraut supper
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Add flour to bacon drippings and blend well.
Stir in sauerkraut; mix well.
Place sauerkraut mixture and bacon pieces into crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir, cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours; high 3 to 4 hours.

title: orange tea punch
directions: In pitcher, combine tea, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar. Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Chill.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter until smooth.
Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls (dip in sprinkles - optional). Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with lightly floured bottom of cup or fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: frosty's salad
directions: Dissolve jello; add all ingredients.
Chill and then top with strawberries!

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish and crab.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Mix and zap again for 45 seconds.

title: donna's caramel corn
directions: Keep popcorn hot in
a 350° oven.
Melt butter; stir in syrup, brown sugar and
salt.
Bring to a boil while stirring. Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn and mix.
Turn into 2 large, greased, shallow pans and place
in	a
oven for 1 hour. Stir	every 5 minutes.	Remove	from
oven.
Cool
and	break apart.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to boil and simmer until desired consistency.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Add 2 teaspoons bottled lemon juice per quart jar and 1 tablespoon garlic powder.
Stir gently.
Seal in jars and process about 15 minutes after water boils in boiling water bath.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add chicken and brown. Add soup, water and vegetable combination.
Heat to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers (do not crush).
In bowl, mix pudding as directed on box.
Then add Cool Whip.
Pour filling onto layer of crackers.
Put crackers on top of filling, then spread icing on top.

title: picky bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place biscuit pieces in a greased Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Melt margarine; add remaining cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
When done place on a plate upside down and serve warm.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening or butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blackberry jam, beating thoroughly.
Sift flour; resift with soda and spices. Add alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each.
Stir in nuts to distribute evenly.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat ingredients till rolling boil, stirring all the time (acts like jelly).
Remove from heat and cool till very cool, using pan of cold water.

title: cold carrot surprise
directions: Mix together soup, sugar, oil, mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Add carrots, onion and pepper.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
In another pan, bring water, bouillon cubes and broccoli to boil until tender.
Pour entire mixture into cheese sauce and serve.

title: lemon rice
directions: Combine stock and water in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir in rice and pepper to taste and bring to a boil.
Immediately reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and let sit 5 minutes, covered.
Sprinkle lemon juice over rice.
Add cilantro and fluff with a fork.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small rectangular sections, brown meat in butter, garlic salt and paprika.
Add bouillon cubes, water, green pepper, onion and tomato.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Ten minutes before done, add soy sauce and flour mixture to thicken. Serve over rice.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place chopped rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix spices and sugar. Pour over rhubarb.
Dot with butter.
Cover with other pie shell. (Place on cookie sheet, juice may boil out.)
Bake at 300° until crust is brown, about 1 hour.

title: southern sugar cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add the following: buttermilk, half and half, melted butter, beaten egg and vanilla.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Then at 350° until slightly soft in middle, about 32 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before putting in the oven.
This makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Combine and spoon into muffin cups (doesn't rise much).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: oodles skillet medley
directions: In a heavy 9-inch skillet (with lid), cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Stir in seasoning packets.
Break up noodles in packages; pour over meat mixture. Add tomatoes with liquid.
Arrange mushrooms on top; simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Soften gelatin in 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Combine jello and sugar with 1 cup hot water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture into gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1 cup cold water. Pour into 8 x 8-inch cake pan and cool.
Chill in refrigerator. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
If doubled, put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bacon egg and cheese muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Grease or spray muffin tins. In medium bowl, combine the flour, bacon, and cheese. Stir to mix. In another bowl, combine the eggs, Ranch dressing, milk and oil. Beat with a fork until well mixed. Combine these two mixtures and stir just until mixed. Do not overmix. Spoon into muffin tins filling each section about 2/3 full. Bake for about 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the muffins. Remove from pan immediately and serve with butter. Makes 10 muffins.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Drain juice off tomatoes; chop 1 1/2 cans tomatoes.
Set aside in bowl.

Blend together 1/2 can tomatoes, peppers, garlic, salt, cumin powder and Worcestershire sauce until it looks like sauce. Pour in bowl with the chopped tomatoes; add onions and sprinkle cilantro until it looks right.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, yet still firm.
Grate cheese. Heat milk with 1/2 cup cheese until cheese melts.
Melt butter in dish.
Pour macaroni in dish and add salt.
Pour milk over macaroni until almost covered.
Sprinkle top with other 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
If desired, broil for few minutes to brown cheese.

title: chocolate pie(over 50 years old)
directions: Mix and cook over heat until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell and brown meringue.

title: cheezy potato casserole
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Dot top with butter. Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Spread with crushed potato chips just before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: otto's onion pie
directions: First make crust, then spread sauce on it.
Put cheese and pepperoni on it last.
Put it in oven for 10 minutes.

title: sure-pop popovers
directions: Combine milk, flour, oil and salt.
Beat with electric beater on high 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 20 seconds after adding each egg.
Grease well 8 (5 ounce) muffin cups or 8 (5 ounce) custard cups.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Set in cold oven.
Turn heat to 425°.
Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Do not open the oven before the 35 minutes are up!
Remove from the oven and let stand a few minutes, then remove from cups.
These can be frozen once made.
To reheat, unwrap and place in a preheated 375° oven.
Heat 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 popovers.

title: acini di pepe fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving liquid- 1 3/4 c. Set pineapple aside.
In a saucepan combine juice, sugar, flour & eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently 8-10 minutes till thick. Cool.
In a large saucepan cook pasta till soft, approx. 12 minutes.
Rinse in cold water & cool.
In bowl combine pasta & cooled sauce.
Add pineapple, oranges, marshmallows & Cool Whip. Stir gently.
Cover & refrigerate overnight.
Makes 20 servings.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add lemon slices and cherry juice. Cook
until
slightly
thickened.	Add
cherries last. Before serving over
ice cream, add most of the bourbon.
In a serving spoon,
flame
some
of
the
remaining bourbon with a match. Slowly transfer the flaming spoonful into the cherries jubilee. (The
pretty
flames
burn	off
alcohol.)	Pour over vanilla ice cream.
All
but
the flaming can be done a day or more before.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Stir together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan (cool).
Add Topping.

title: apple pizza
directions: Flatten biscuit dough and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle on chopped apples, cheese, brown sugar, and slices of margarine. Bake at 400° for 10-12 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Make meatballs; combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft).
I shape into walnut size balls.
Place on waxed paper and freeze.
Store in freezer until ready to use.

title: ham fritters with creamy sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir in eggs and milk. Add shortening; mix well.
Stir in ham.
Drop batter by tablespoon into deep oil heated to 375°.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with Creamy Sauce.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: cherry lemon cheese cake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour in pie shell. Chill three hours. When you serve, add cool whip and 1 Tbsp cherry filling to the top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream softened margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Alternately add flour mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Drop teaspoon of dough onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetarian taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except taco chips.
Add them just before serving.

title: strawberry pecan scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yogurt, stirring until ingredients are moistened (dough will be sticky). Turn dough onto floured surface, knead 4 to 5 times.
Pat dough into 8 inch circle on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Cut dough into 12 wedges, cutting to but not through; make slit in each wedge.
Place 1 teaspoon strawberry spread on top of each slit; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes.

title: lamb ragout(stew)
directions: Wash lamb and pat dry, season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll in flour.
Brown meat in heavy pot, in which oil has been heated.
After browning on all sides, remove from pan; set aside.
Drain oil from pan.
Add onion, garlic and meat.
Cover with water.
Cook on medium heat for one hour in covered pot. After cooking one hour, add sherry to stew.
Cook on low heat 1/2 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: never fail creamy fudge
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add milk and butter; stir until well blended.
Place over direct low heat and cook until small amount dropped in water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and set in a pan of cold water, without stirring or shaking the pan.
Cool until you can place your hand comfortably on the bottom of the pans; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Begin beating and continue until candy begins to hold shape.
Pour into buttered plate or pan.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix,
oil, cream cheese and eggs with mixer. Fold in berries and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased and floured pan. Bake
at
350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let set in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on rack.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Test with butter knife, when it comes out clean, the pudding is done.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot rhubarb.
Add other ingredients and jell.
Serves 10 to 11.

title: jalapeno chili bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: frickadella's
directions: Mix all ingredients and form to the size of a large meat ball.
Place in frying pan and flatten with fork.
Cook until done.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for chewy brownies.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until set.

title: english pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy date squares
directions: Beat
eggs
until
light.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Combine biscuit mix and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x
2-inch pan.
Bake	at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into 16 squares.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Top with potato chips.
Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar and press in baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar and spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Spread pie filling (any flavor) over cream cheese mixture and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies and pour Kahlua over brownies.
Set aside.
Beat or break Skor bars in a food processor.

title: eggplant maurice
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, pepper and garlic salt; set aside. Place layer of eggplant in a greased casserole.
Add layer of tomatoes and some of the chopped green pepper and onion.
Add layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled, ending with the cheese.
Cover and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes. Uncover, reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for another 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: no shortening pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch air bake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May also be used as a sandwich spread.

title: spinach waldorf salad
directions: Place fresh spinach in large bowl.
add red and yellow apple cubes, walnuts and raisins.
Tos well with dressing.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top of salad.
Delicious with cooked and cubed chicken breast meat added to salad.
Makes 2 to 3 main course salads or 6 side dish salads.

title: deer hunter's pie
directions: Saute the hamburger in a skillet until it is lightly browned and completely separated.
Arrange a layer of potatoes over the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Follow with a layer of meat, a layer of onions and a layer of apples.
Repeat until you have used up all of the ingredients.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn on cob just enough to set milk, about 3 minutes. Cut from cob.
Put cabbage, onions and peppers through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Combine all vegetables.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add peanut butter and vanilla, stir well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Form into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Press fork into flour and then press cookie ball with fork to make waffle design.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15-18 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: greek-style cheese ball
directions: Bring cream and Feta cheeses to room temperature.
Cut the Feta cheese into chunks.
In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine cheeses.
Cover and blend or process until smooth. Reserve 1 tablespoon of the olives and 1 tablespoon of the onion. Chop remaining olives.
Stir the chopped olives, remaining onion and basil into cheese mixture.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Sprinkle cheese ball with reserved green onion and black olive slices.
Serve with pita bread triangles.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: party mix(microwave)
directions: In a small bowl, add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted butter.
Mix well.
Set aside.
In a large Ziploc bag, mix Chex cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Pour butter mixture over cereal. Close bag and shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents into a microwaveproof bowl and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: raisin bread
directions: Warm milk in
a
saucepan to 70° (lukewarm).
Add yeast and allow to
dissolve,
then
add sugar, mixing well.
Slowly mix in flour followed by eggs, butter, salt and lemon zest.

title: crescent-roll chicken
directions: Mix together chicken and cream cheese.
Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Put cream cheese mixture in crescent rolls and roll over.
Put melted butter on outside of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: christmas celery
directions: Mash avocado.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Blend in cheese, lemon rind, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stuff celery. Garnish with pimento.
Yields 1 cup cheese mixture.

title: hawaiian fruitcake
directions: Use wooden spoon to mix.
Sift flour, soda and salt in large bowl.
Add sugar, eggs and pineapple to flour mixture.
Add nuts. Mix with wooden spoon until moist.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chicken and vegetables in lemon-mustard sauce
directions: In 9-inch skillet heat oil; add chicken and cook, turning once, until browned, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer chicken to plate and set aside.

In same skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add vegetables and garlic and saute, stirring frequently, until onions are translucent, 4 to 5 minutes. Add sherry and bring to a boil; stir in water, mustard, lemon juice and broth mix.
Add potatoes and chicken to skillet and return mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and let simmer until chicken is tender and, when pierced with a fork, juices run clear, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Add oleo and milk.
Do not stir. Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Stir to mix.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: lettuce-wrapped picadillo
directions: *You may substitute 1/2 cup each chopped onion and green pepper and 1 rib celery, minced, rather than buying the frozen mixture.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, boiling water and shortening and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Now, mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Form loaves and let rise.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: mustard paste pickles and dressing
directions: Cut up vegetables and soak in salt water overnight.
Cook in salt water and drain.
Do not overcook.
Set aside.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Melt cheese in crock-pot.
Add dressing and sausage.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello in cottage cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend in flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Slice carrots about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling water until just tender; drain.
In skillet, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly and stir until cranberry sauce melts.
Add drained carrots; stir until glazed on all sides, about 5 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and pepper in large bowl.
Sprinkle salt over top.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Let stand at room temperature for one hour.
Drain in strainer.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add to cabbage mixture and refrigerate.

title: sausage cornbread dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package. Cool and crumble.

title: double pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, Karo syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Pour into pie crust.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix until crumbly the first 3 ingredients.
Add the egg with 6 tablespoons water and the vinegar to crumbly mix.
Stir and form into 3 large balls. Chill or freeze until ready to use.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except the egg yolk. Mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut a cross in top of dough.
Brush with egg yolk mixed with a little water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hollow sound when tapped.

title: tortellini chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add tortellini, chicken and vegetables.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dutch spinach salad
directions: Place spinach and onion in a large serving bowl.
Set aside. In a skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Remove from heat.
