Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and black pepper.
Bring to the boiling point.
Slowly pour hot dressing over spinach and onion.
Toss and serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mezette
directions: Cook in microwave.
Cook noodles a little bit before using. Crumble ground beef and onions and put in baking dish for microwave.
Cook for 6 minutes on High.
Stir in chili powder; add noodles on top.
Mix together mushroom soup, water and tomato soup.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook 10 minutes on High and 20 minutes on Medium.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix in large bowl.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 of the eggs.
Mix well.
Pat into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: In heavy saucepan on low heat, melt together margarine, caramels and milk.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Bake 1/2 of the batter in greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Pour slightly cooled caramel mixture over baked half of cake.
Pour remaining cake batter over the caramel layer. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kochanny chili
directions: Brown the beef in a cooking pot. Dissolve the bouillon cubes in the warm water and add to the meat.
Chop the green peppers, onion and celery sticks.
Add to the pot along with the whole hot pepper. Don't break it up as you will remove it later on. Sprinkle on the chili powder and sugar. Add the tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce and garlic.
Mix all ingredients well. Slowly simmer chili for about 1 1/2 hours. When it is done, remove the hot pepper.

title: vinegar pie(early pioneers)
directions: Combine vinegar, water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add butter and stir until it melts.
Mix the flour with a little of the cold water until smooth.
Add slowly to the boiling liquid and stir until thickened.
Pour filling into pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with strips of pastry in a crisscross fashion.
Bake at 450° for 16 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cook bacon and remove.
Saute onions and green peppers in bacon grease.
Pour juice from tomatoes into onions and peppers.
Then add flour, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir until it becomes thick.
Then add green beans to mixture.
Cook until beans are done.
Now, pour into a casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Before serving, you can reheat it in the microwave for about 8 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eloise's baked chicken
directions: Mix last five ingredients.
Dip chicken and tap off excess on side of bowl.
Place chicken in covered (Tupperware or Rubbermaid) bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Place coffee and rum in a pan; bring to a simmer.
Add chocolate and butter.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until all are melted.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs. Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is thick.
Beat in vanilla and chocolate mixture.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat into chocolate mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Transfer to rack to cool overnight.

title: perry's surprise
directions: Brown hamburger over medium heat.
Add other ingredients until hot.
Serve with crackers or by itself.
"Great for cold, wintery evenings."

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water according to directions.
Drain. Stir onion mix into sour cream and add sweet milk.
Combine with tuna and noodles and pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake about 30 minutes at 400° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bean-pasta soup
directions: In small skillet or saucepan, saute green pepper, onion, garlic and basil in the oil until onion is tender.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook macaroni in the boiling water with 1/4 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes, or until macaroni is tender (do not drain).
Add green pepper mixture, canned soup and beans to macaroni and water; mix well, then heat thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add the lemon juice.
Sprinkle with anchovies, if used.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of asparagus in bottom of dish.
Put 1/2 of soup on top.
Cut eggs and place on soup, then asparagus, then soup.
Put cheese on then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Blend.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: deborah rohlack's cap'n crunch bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Remove from stove top and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Pour this over cereal in large bowl.
Mix together, then drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, flour, salt and juice from pineapple and oranges in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Mixture will be like sauce, not thick like pudding.
While sauce is cooking, cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse well.
Cool the sauce; add macaroni. Mix well in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add pineapple, oranges, cherries (drained) and Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: no fail pie dough
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, salt and sugar.
Cut the shortening into the flour mixture until crumbly.
Beat the egg; add water and vinegar to the egg and blend the mixture into the flour mixture until all of the flour is moist.
Don't overbeat.
Let the mixture rest for 10 minutes to insure tenderness.
Makes pastry for a 2-crust pie.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Grind squash and onion. Add salt.
Mix and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and cook in kettle on top of stove for 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: old fashioned chicken 'n noodles
directions: In large pan, place chicken, water, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
Measure broth; add enough hot water to make 6 cups.
Return to pan.
Add celery, carrots and onion.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.
Heat to boiling; add noodles.
Boil 5 to 7 minutes uncovered or until noodles are tender.
Add chicken; heat thoroughly.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 16 to 20 balls.
Brown on all sides in hot butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to boil.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit
directions: Cut up fruit.
Pour peach pie filling over fruit.
Stir well. Refrigerate.

title: minute meat loaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and place in microwave casserole dish.
(Save
a
little
tomato sauce to spread on top of hamburger
mixture.)
Cover with wax paper and cook 15 minutes on High in microwave, turning halfway into cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers in a large casserole.
Pour crushed pineapple over wafers.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and vanilla flavoring in saucepan on medium heat.
Stir continuously until it boils.
Pour mixture over pineapple and wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, cheese and seasoning.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli; cook 1 minute longer.
Add mushrooms and almonds.
Serve hot with chips or crackers.
Can be served in a round loaf or shepherd's bread.
Cut top off; remove insides.
Pour mixture into bread.
Use center of bread to dip.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat softened butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute zucchini in hot oil and butter until lightly browned.
Arrange zucchini, slightly overlapping in baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper, then with bread crumbs.
Cover with sauce and then with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: betty's "love" soup(minestrone)
directions: Combine steak, cabbage, water, onions, celery, carrots, kidney beans, tomatoes and seasonings in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 2 hours.

title: caramel pudding
directions: In a heavy pot, brown 1/2 cupful of sugar very brown, then add 2 1/2 cupfuls of boiling water, 1 cupful of sugar, a lump of butter the size of an egg and a pinch of salt.
Boil for 10 minutes.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Add whichever optional ingredients you like.
Be creative. Use a blender and add crushed ice.
Put ingredients into blender one at a time and then blend to puree consistency.
Add the additional, optional ingredients if you like.
You may experiment and one at a time.
Taste and experiment. .
.Delicious!
If too thick, more juice; if too thin, add an additional banana.
Serve immediately!
Makes 4 (8-ounce) portions.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Layer salmon, crackers and dots of butter in a greased casserole dish, ending with crackers.
Add enough milk just to cover.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: beau monde vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve chilled with vegetables or chips.

title: barbecue franks
directions: Mix together mustard, brown sugar, onion and garlic salt. Then add the rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour (on stove top). Put in crock-pot.
Add franks (where sauce is covered).
Cook on slow until hot.

title: fruit and cake dessert
directions: Use fruit desired, 20 ounces apricots, blueberries or strawberries (fresh, frozen or canned).
Use 1/3 cup sugar (if desired).
Cut or crumble angel food cake in oblong pan.
Spread prepared pudding over this and spread Cool Whip over top of cake and pudding.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, small jar pimento and black olives to ground beef; cook until onion and pepper are tender.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cook until bubbly.
Add to macaroni; bake in casserole at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake(fun for kids to help make)
directions: Mix crust.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruity baked beans
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 4 whole pineapple rings, and chop remaining rings into quarters.
Combine pineapple quarters, pork and beans, bacon, ketchup, brown sugar, molasses, onion, cloves and garlic.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake.
Place remaining pineapple rings on top of casserole and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake five minutes, or until brown.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Mix with rest of ingredients and spread on muffins.
Chill for at least 1 hour.* Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut each muffin half into 4 to 6 pieces.

title: rice flake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons and flatten.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: overnight crab casserole
directions: Drain crabmeat and flake coarsely.
Combine crab, macaroni, cheese, eggs and undiluted soup, milk and chives.
Put in deep 1-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerated at least 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with paprika; season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ice cream sodas
directions: For each serving place syrup or ice cream topping or crushed fruit and sugar in a tall glass.
Fill half full with chilled sparkling water.
Add scoop of ice cream.
Stir.
Fill glass with sparkling water.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel, halve, gut and thinly slice the cucumbers, being careful to taste each one, as a bitter one will spoil the whole dish. Wash and drain the shrimp. In a bowl mix, in order, the sugar, salt, garlic press full of fresh ginger (squeeze into the bowl, as all you need is the juice) and the vinegar. Mix vigorously and pour over the cucumbers and shrimp. Stir together. Chill for a minimum of 2 hours prior to serving. Mix frequently. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve. Serves 4.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: You can use fat-free ingredients.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Cook roast into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Mix other ingredients; add meat and marinade at least 24 hours.
Grill on kabobs.
Great with grilled tomatoes, onions, green peppers, mushrooms, etc.
Makes enough marinade for 1 1/2 to 2 pounds meat.

title: sunday sandwiches
directions: In large skillet over low heat, make a roux with butter and flour.
Add broth, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Increase to medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add more broth is sauce is too thick.
Add beef and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve open-faced on toasted and buttered kaiser rolls.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature.
Blend with electric mixer.
Add onion, A.1. sauce and 1 cup pecan pieces.
Chill mixture until firm enough to mold.
Make into a ball the size of a grapefruit.
Roll the cheese ball in pecans (chopped fine) and parsley flakes.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve on party platter with crackers.

title: carrot-granola muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and allspice until blended.
In a separate large bowl, mix cereal, brown sugar and buttermilk.
Let stand for 5 minutes for granola to absorb the milk.

title: holiday bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cook in boiling water, covered, until they are tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Add salt to taste to water while cooking.
When potatoes are soft, cut in pieces and mash with electric beater.
Add butter and mix.
Add bourbon and blend to the mashed potatoes.

title: fat-free guacamole dip
directions: Cook peas until just tender; drain and cool.
Place the peas in a food processor fitted with the steel chopping blade.
Process until smooth.
Add the mayonnaise, garlic, onion, lemon juice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Process to blend.
Scrape into a bowl, cover and chill.
Yields 2 cups.
One tablespoon equals 21 calories, 4 grams fat.

title: blue's okra gumbo
directions: Smother okra in 1/2 cup oil, stirring frequently until no longer stringy.
Mix the smothered okra with the other ingredients, adding water to get the desired consistency.
Add roux and bring to a boil.
Simmer until the meats are done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend
Crisco and sugar until creamy; beat in egg yolks one at a	time.
Combine	soda,
salt and buttermilk;
add to creamed mixture.
Add
flour.
Fold
in
stiffly
beaten
egg whites;
add lemon extract.
Pour into large tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add all ingredients except bread crumbs and 1/4 cup cheese for topping; mix.
Add bread crumbs and cheese and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Feeds 8 to 10 people.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle hard-boiled eggs, ham and cheese in bottom of pan.
Combine beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over filling. Bake until mixture is set, about 35 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: chicken tex-ana
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove bone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
In saucepan, combine other ingredients.
cook all together with soup for 10 minutes.
Mix chicken, spaghetti, soup mixture and 2 cups grated cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in well buttered casserole dish at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt the butter in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add the onions and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring often until well browned.
Add the garlic and the flour.
Stir until the flour is no longer white.
Add the broth, water and pepper.
Stir well and bring to a boil.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs one at a time and cream.
Add the wafers and milk alternately.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Cook in well-greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake can be made a couple of days ahead of serving.
Freezes well.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Remove skin and pulp from watermelon, leaving white rind. Cut into small cubes to make 16 cups.
Parboil in hot water to cover in pan for 15 minutes or until fork-tender; drain.
Mix rest of ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rind. Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Reserve syrup.
Bring to a boil. Pour over rind.
Repeat for 3 more days.
Heat rind and syrup in pan on fourth day.
Spoon into hot sterilized jars.
Seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: summer cool punch
directions: Combine both drinks in large bowl.
(If you only have a smaller bowl, split just the drink recipes.)
Spoon on ice cream and sherbet.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in two 8-inch pans. Cool.
Split layers to make 4 layers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir in spinach and water chestnuts; chill. Serve with crackers or Hawaiian bread.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and serve with vegetables.

title: squash fritters
directions: Chop squash and onion fine.
Add pepper, sugar, flour, beaten eggs and margarine.
Mix well.
Shape into cakes.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Serve warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place in microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Put back into microwave on high for 4 more minutes.
Take out, and add margarine and vanilla.
Put back in microwave for 2 additional minutes on high.
Add baking soda and stir.
Pour contents into a buttered shallow pan.	When cooled break into smaller pieces.

title: peppers and hot dogs
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and ketchup.
Pour over peppers. Cook on medium heat until peppers wilt, then add hot dogs.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in jars.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in tomato, okra and basil. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: tomorrow cake
directions: Mix cake mix (dry), 1 egg and margarine (softened).
Press into a long cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Pour pecans over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by the spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, cover raisins with water; cook slowly until plumped and water is almost gone.
Make mixture of sugar, salt, cornstarch and 1/4 cup milk.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add small amount of cornstarch mixture to raisins; stir.
Alternately add remaining mixture and 3/4 cup milk; cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Top with favorite meringue and bake at 350° until a golden brown.

title: snappy liver dip
directions: Combine sour cream and soup mix and let stand about 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sauces and mix well.
Add sour cream mixture and mix.
Add liver sausage and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry pretzel salad dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and put in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool crust completely.

title: warm blue cheese dip
directions: Cook bacon 7 minutes; drain.
Add garlic and cook until bacon is crisp.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth. Stir in bacon, Blue cheese and chives.
Transfer to baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chop all other ingredients, except cranberries.
Chop cranberries in blender.
Add chopped ingredients to jello mixture.
Pour all in large glass bowl to jell.
Chill until set.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: In a large saucepan, boil 1 cup raisins in 2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Add butter or margarine and let it cool.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind ham in food processor.
Add pickle relish, mayonnaise and boiled eggs.

title: asparagus with sunshine sauce
directions: Cook fresh asparagus or use 2 packages frozen, cooked, or 2 (15-ounce) cans heated and drained.

title: the alpine(date-nut roll)
directions: Cut marshmallows and pour water over them. Add milk, nuts, dates and cracker crumbs. Knead with hands. Form into roll and wrap with wax paper. Refrigerate for a few hours. Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: instant baked potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to directions on package (omit butter).
Add cream cheese and beaten egg to the prepared potatoes.
Beat well.
Add onion and parsley.
Blend well.
Place in a well-greased 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: Place tortillas in oven.
Heat to 425°.
Have a shallow 2 qt. baking dish ready.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Blend fruit and yogurt together with Cool Whip and pour into pie crust. Freeze. Thaw slightly before serving (about 2 hours). Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in plastic Ziploc bag and refrigerate.
Prepare filling as for fruit pies.
Pinch off small amount of dough and roll into a ball.
Roll out in a circle about as large as a saucer; crimp edges.
Fry in deep boiling fat; drain on paper towels.
These can be used as a fund raising project.

title: chicken and shells
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Add milk and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a baking dish, cover and bake 30 minutes at 350° (if more cheese is desired, add Velveeta on top).

title: corn fritters
directions: Add milk to corn, flour, salt, pepper, sugar and baking powder.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Drop by spoon into hot oil. Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: clam chowder(fast and easy)
directions: Mix all canned soups in medium size pot; add butter and cream and slowly heat to almost boiling (watch it; it burns very quickly).
Add clams with juice and slowly heat to boiling again. Ready to serve.

title: oatmeal candies
directions: Boil at full rolling boil for 1 minute the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper.

title: cabbage-mac soup*
directions: Pour the water in a large pot, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until macaroni is tender, about 20 minutes. (Serves 4.)

title: snicker bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Boil together for 2 minutes the margarine, brown sugar and white syrup. Remove from heat and add the dry roasted peanuts. Pour over crackers. Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with the chocolate chips. Spread when melted.

title: beef stew dish
directions: Boil chipped beef in pressure cooker until done (in seasoning).
Put into large container on stove and add the tomatoes, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook until ingredients are done to taste.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt butter and sugar over medium heat until smooth.
Let cool.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Great for dipping apples and strawberries.

title: almond bark drops
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Mix all ingredients. Pour melted coating over all and drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Makes at least 2 to 3 coffee cans full.

title: auntie's squash and potatoes
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
While butter is heating, roll potatoes, onion and squash in corn meal.
Add rolled vegetables to butter and fry to desired tenderness.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over the top and serve.

title: pie filling cake
directions: Beat eggs; mix in white cake mix.
Fold in pie filling.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: betty's tomato gravy
directions: Cover the bottom of your iron frying pan with fried meat grease.
Sprinkle thick with flour.
Add water and let gravy simmer a minute.
Add salt, black pepper and canned or fresh ripe tomatoes.
Stir up real good.
Serve hot with plenty of biscuits for soppin'.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo/butter.
Mix corn, eggs, onions and peppers together.
Stir in muffin mix.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: russian salad dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients well.
Serve on tossed salad.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and add the dressing and Salad Supreme. Add tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, olives, meats and/or cheese, etc., to suit your preference.
Cut all ingredients into small pieces.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: hot spiced apple juice
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to the boiling point.
Let simmer 10 minutes, then strain.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine pork chops, water, chopped vegetables and salt, red pepper and black pepper to taste.
Bring to boil; let simmer until pork chops are tender.
Drain broth; set aside.
Combine 1 1/2 cups broth and 1 1/4 cups uncooked rice.
Cook until tender.
Combine can of cream of mushroom or cream of chicken soup, rice and pork chops.
You should have a nice creamy casserole.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 2 ingredients and roll into a ball.
Roll in cracked pepper.

title: rock and roll no bake cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, cocoa and milk to a soft ball stage (2 minutes).
Add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on waxed paper to cool.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine cider, brown sugar, salt and nutmeg in saucepan.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and add to cider.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot with orange slices.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to directions on box.
Cook bacon separately.
Combine beans, bacon and tomatoes; add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Gently pull off cabbage leaves; simmer in 1 inch boiling water for 5 minutes, covered.
(Or you may take the core out of cabbage and microwave whole head for 9 minutes.
The leaves will pull off easily.)
Drain and lay out ready for filling.
Combine meat, egg, onion, rice and seasoning.
Fill leaves loosely with mixture, roll up and place in 9-inch skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese, pour on tomatoes and cook until steam appears.
Then turn to low heat for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop large teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on box.
While warm, punch holes in cake and pour creme de menthe over cake.
Let stand overnight.

title: favorite chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (on high 5 or 6 hours).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk, pepper and onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab meat hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix and spread on party rye or pumpernickel bread.
Broil until bubbly and slightly browned.
Makes 36.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift 3 1/2 cups flour; combine creamed margarine and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each. Coat candy and nuts with remaining flour; mix buttermilk and soda. Add to flour mix. Pour into greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 230° to 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours. Put pan of water on low rack to keep cake moist.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in order given.
(I mix them in the blender.)
Pour into pastry lined pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 more minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.
Cool. Refrigerate.

title: okra and seafood gumbo
directions: In large heavy pot, fry sliced smoked sausage in bacon fat or drippings.
Add ham; fry a few minutes longer.
Remove meat.
Fry onions, garlic and shallots for a few minutes, then add sliced okra and fry well.
Do not burn.
Add celery, parsley, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves, seasoning, ham and smoked sausage.
Let cook a few minutes.
Add about 3 quarts of hot water; cook 30 minutes.
Brown flour in bacon fat until dark brown.
Remove from fire.
Stir in 2 cups cold water; add to pot.
Stir and cook 20 minutes.
Add crabs, shrimp and lemon slices; cook until thick as gravy.
Serve with cooked rice.
(More water may be added for right consistency.)

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bake potato dish
directions: Mix altogether, except bacon.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: oven fries
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake on a baking sheet at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: "bulji"(bread)
directions: Slowly add enough flour to make a soft dough, knead for a few minutes. Let rise until double in size. Knead down and let rise again. Put in pan. Let it rise again. Bake for 40-45 minutes at 350°F.
Makes one loaf.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 7 minutes (varies depending on wattage of microwave). Stir in the butter and vanilla.
Cook about 2 minutes and add the soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Blend in egg yolks. Spread 1 cup
graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch dish.
Pour egg yolk mixture over crumbs.
Cover with another light layer
of
crumbs
cup).
Whip heavy cream until stiff.
Add
pineapple,
walnuts,
sugar
and
vanilla. Spread whipped cream
mixture over top layer of crumbs.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: easy luscious roast
directions: Spray Pam in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper roast (thawed or frozen).
Place in dish.
Pour soup over roast.
Cover.
Place in 250° oven.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours.
Delish!
Easy!

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Blend and refrigerate.
Serve in frosted glasses.

title: fellowship dinner beans
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain beans and add to meat mixture.
Mix together.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Turn into large casserole dish and top with any kind of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal goulash
directions: Brown veal in hot oil in heavy saucepot or Dutch oven.
Tie bay leaf, caraway seed and pepper in cheesecloth bag.
Add broth, carrots, salt and the spice bag to veal.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour, or until veal is tender, stirring occasionally.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter in skillet until onions are tender, but not browned.
Add to meat mixture and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Blend flour into cold water.
Stir into liquid in saucepot.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Discard spice bag.
Gently stir in paprika and sour cream and heat, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pear butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover and cook on high 10-12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecue water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap around chestnuts.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Drain most of the grease. Mix sauce and pour over chestnuts.
Bake another 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip for crackers
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: In skillet, saute links with pepper.
Stir in sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: toni's zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend together in order: eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini, lemon rind and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Add walnuts.
Divide batter into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: beef onion casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Combine jello and pineapple in saucepan.
Heat until simmering.
Add sugar, baby food and cut up cheese.
Mix, but do not beat.
Chill until it mounds when dropped from spoon.
Add Cool Whip slowly.
Blend, but do not whip.
Pour into pan or dish. Cover with nuts.
Chill.

title: carrot gelatin dessert
directions: Use only 1/2 amount of water to prepare Jell-O.
When Jell-O is dissolved, add carrots and pineapple.
Put into mold or bowl and let cool.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Wash and cut unpeeled cucumbers into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix water and lime and put in cucumbers to soak overnight.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs and mix well. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: brownies with mix
directions: Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Double for a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
